title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth. Store in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 cups.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine salad dressing and Italian dressing; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: fillets thermidor
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Roll fish in a two-quart casserole.
Pour milk over fish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until easily flaked with a fork, but moist.
Take it out of oven.

title: spicy rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Drain.
Layer in baking dish. Mix cheese, chilies (add a little of the juice) and sour cream in a bowl.
Pour over rice.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Cover with lid when top starts to brown.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve
jello in hot water and add other ingredients. Chill overnight.	(Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.)

title: navajo fry bread(makes 6)
directions: Mix flour, dry milk, baking powder and salt.
With fingers, crumble in lard until like cornmeal.
Add water; stir with a fork until dough clings together.
Turn out on floured board and knead 4 or 5 minutes.
Divide dough into 6 portions; shape each into a ball.
On a floured board, press out 1 ball to a 6 to 7-inch round and cover loosely.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Deep-fry rounds in hot oil as directed.
Drain on paper towels; serve hot.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and extract, then add Seven-Up last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(You may have to adjust baking time according to your individual oven.)

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Drain fat.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Put beans in casserole dish and pour mixture over top, but do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: flaky crunchers
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in skillet and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and cornflakes.
Continue stirring until all are coated with syrup mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: dream pies
directions: Mix all together and divide into the 2 shells.
Bake at 350° until brown (approximately 45 minutes).

title: b c roll-ups
directions: Roll each slice of bread with a rolling pin until flattened. Spread each slice with mayonnaise and top with one slice of bologna and one slice of cheese.
Roll each into a log and cut crosswise into about 5 pieces.
Keep together with a toothpick, if necessary.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium baking dish, put margarine or butter.
Put in oven to melt and heat.
Heat fruit or berries.

title: creamy easter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese. Gradually beat in cold milk until smooth. Add water and pudding mix. Beat until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping and pour into crust.

title: doro wot
directions: Saute onion in a little oil.
Stir in tomato paste, pepper, Berbere, salt and 1 pint of water.
Crush in chicken stock. Simmer 30 minutes.
Add chicken and eggs.
Simmer 10 more minutes. Serve with rice.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to boil
for exactly 5 minutes, 2 - 1 lb boxes of powdered sugar and 1 cup of water.

title: best banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter. Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix thoroughly. Add bananas to flour mixture.
Add to creamed mixture gradually. Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
Let stand in pan for a few minutes, then remove from pans and cool completely.

title: rose hip jam
directions: To prepare rose hips, remove the stem and blossom ends with a sharp knife, then make a slit down each side of the hip and remove the seeds.
Chop seedless hips rather coarsely.
Add sugar to prepared hips and stir, stir, stir until sugar is dissolved.
Mix water and pectin; bring to a rolling boil and boil hard for one minute.
Stir the pectin mix quickly but thoroughly into the sweetened rose hips and quickly pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: easy little cheesecake
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla wafers and pie filling for 5 minutes.
Put 1 wafer in each paper, then add the pie filling (use petit four pan and paper liners).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool and add 1 teaspoon of cherry pie filling to each cheesecake.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugars and cream thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to cream mixture; shape into rolls (1 1/2-inch round).
Wrap in wax paper and chill for 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices and bake in 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Put in big pot.
Add chili beans, tomato sauce, water, Texas chili seasoning and chili-style tomatoes.
Seasonings can be used on hamburger when browning. Cayenne pepper to taste.
Heat on medium 15 to 20 minutes or until beans are tender and chili warm.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour into crust and bake for 8 minutes.
Cool, chill, then top with Cool Whip.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Toss. Pile lightly into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: english pie
directions: Keep egg whites and whip until stiff.
Mix egg yolks and other ingredients together.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into a pie crust. Bake at 350° until set.

title: rice casserole
directions: Spray casserole with cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients in casserole.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours, covered at 350 degrees.

title: sherry rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup, Swiss cheese and sherry.
Heat until warm.
Add rice, spinach, water chestnuts, lemon juice, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn into well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: martha washington balls
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into small balls.
Chill overnight in covered container.
Dip each ball by toothpick into melted mixture made of dipping chocolate with enough paraffin to make a thin mixture.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix altogether and mix well.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes at 375°.
Serves 16.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook blueberries and sugar for about 5 minutes.
Thicken with the cornstarch.
Remove from the heat.
Add the almond extract; set aside to cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Wash and peel zucchini.
Cut in half and scrape seeds from middle and grate.
Combine all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: marble squares
directions: Blend sugar, butter, vanilla, egg and dry ingredients.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onions in a medium size pot. Drain thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 25 minutes before serving. Garnish with sour cream, black olives and parsley flakes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: garden chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook until corn is tender.

title: brandy slush
directions: Freeze in covered container.
To serve, after freezes fill glass 3/4 full of slush and 7-Up to fill glass.

title: salmon tetrazzini
directions: Layer salmon in bottom of buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer onions on salmon.
Layer mushrooms on onions.

Break spaghetti into 2-inch length pieces and layer uncooked on top of mushrooms. Take tomato soup, mushroom soup, 4 cups water and 1/2 pound Velveeta (cut into chunks) and heat in saucepan until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Slice 1/4 pound Velveeta and layer it over top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.
This casserole can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Saute bacon over medium heat until bacon is almost cooked. Add onion and cook until soft.
Add cream and chives.
In mixer, beat potatoes until they are just crumbly; add cream mixture and eggs.
Roll in parchment paper and slice into cakes.
Saute in a little oil until brown on both sides.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Spread dip on large plate.
Peel and mash avocados.
Spread over dip.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; spread over avocados.
Add chopped onion, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese.
Chill overnight.
Serve at room temperature.

title: chocolate crumb cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square baking pan.
In large mixing bowl, stir together flour and sugar.
Remove 1/2 cup mixture; set aside for topping.
Stir baking soda, baking powder and salt into remaining flour mixture.
Add butter, egg, milk and syrup; beat until well blended.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Sprinkle reserved flour mixture over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil the sweet potatoes, when nearly done, peel, slice and place in layer in a shallow baking dish.
Melt the sugar and oleo. Put a tablespoon of the sugar-oleo mixture on each slice.
Add the hot water and bake 3/4 hour in 350° oven, basting often.

title: vegetable relish
directions: Chop all the vegetables up and mix together.
Sprinkle with pickling salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse vegetables and drain. Combine sugar, spices, vinegar and water, then pour over vegetables.
Bring to a boil, boiling gently for 5 minutes.
Fill hot canning jars to within 1/2-inch of tops.
Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
(Start timing when water returns to boil.)

title: ranch chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine
sugar and condensed milk.
Stir in granulated chocolate mixed to a paste in a little hot water.
Stir like crazy.
Add heavy whipping cream.
Add half and half.
Freeze in a 1 1/2-gallon freezer.

title: quick pork chops
directions: Combine.
Place pork chops into Pyrex baking dish.
Cover with the sauce.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until tender.

title: baked apples(serves 4; 0 fat, 0 cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small pan, heat wine and juice until mixture comes to a boil.
Turn heat off and add raisins and cinnamon.
Stir; cover and let sit for 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread on large serving platter.
Pour salsa over that and layer remaining ingredients: onion, pepper, tomato, lettuce, cheese and top with olives.

title: mabel's caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Spread corn in two pans.
Melt oleo and stir in brown sugar and salt.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and soda.
Pour over corn.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool and store in plastic bags that seal well.

title: zucchini lasagne
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown beef and onions in skillet.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, mushrooms, garlic, basil, parsley, salt, pepper and oregano.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Combine cottage cheese, zucchini and egg.
In large baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese mixture, meat mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese after removing from oven.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Place in round casserole.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add sugar and stir.
Add lemon and pineapple juice.
Chill till slightly jelled.
Add remaining ingredients, stir, pour into mold and chill.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Stir in next 3 ingredients. Mix well. Mix together buttermilk, soda and vanilla and add to the first ingredients. Add eggs and mix well. Bake in greased pan at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake is done.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onions and peppers in butter. Add tomatoes and soup. Add salt and pepper to taste and seasoning. Simmer over low heat. Add shrimp; cook until shrimp are done. Serve over rice.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and set aside.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, soup, 1 stick melted butter, cheese and onion.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Mix corn flakes and 1/2 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Put potatoes in blender.
Combine milk, eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla, salt and most of the butter.
Add potatoes in small chunks, a few at a time.
Pour into Pyrex dish.
Top with remaining butter and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy chicken kiev
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Melt 1/2 cup butter with 1/2 teaspoon garlic salt.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 65 to 75 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry chopped onion in 1 tablespoon cooking oil until golden brown.
Add frozen peas and carrots.
Stir-fry until done.
Add salt and ground pepper to taste.
Remove from pan.
Brown garlic in the remaining cooking oil.
Add dried mushrooms, tofu, soy sauce and salt.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add cooked rice and mixed vegetables.
Mix and heat thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: caramel coffee rings
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; beat egg and add to mixture, stirring to blend.
Sift flour, measure and resift with baking powder.
Add to other mixture, then add nuts.
Turn batter into 8-inch square buttered pan and bake in a slow oven (300°) for 25 minutes, until brown.
Cut squares.
Makes 12 or 16 squares.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients in mixing bowl; mix well. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Set oven on 350° and bake until done.

title: tuna steaks with olive oil and thyme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
If necessary, trim dark parts from tuna.
In a small bowl, combine thyme, oil and black pepper into a smooth paste and rub into each piece of fish.
Place fish in an ovenproof glass baking dish and bake, uncovered, until cooked through, 30 to 45 minutes, depending on thickness.
Place fish on serving platter and serve hot, strewn with pepper slivers, with lime wedges on the side.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan and line with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk; beat 2 minutes. Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture over crackers and then put on another layer of crackers and the rest of the pudding on top of the crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: cheese roll
directions: Allow cheese to soften for 30 minutes. Mix cheeses and nuts. Roll into balls, then roll balls in the chili powder or sprinkle on chili powder.

title: chicken parmesan over rice
directions: Put rice in bottom of rectangle pan; sprinkle seasonings on. Heat together 3 cans of soup.
Pour over rice.
Lay skinned chicken on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook, covered, at 275° for 1 hour, then, uncovered, for 2 hours.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook together blueberries, 1/2 cup sugar, water and cornstarch about 2 minutes or until thickened.
Whip the cream cheese (room temperature) and 4x sugar, then mix in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells and top with blueberry mixture.
Makes 2 pies.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all together well except sauce.
Form into balls.
Cover bottom of large pot with sauce.
Add meatballs gently.
Add rest of sauce.
Cook over medium-low heat, turning gently every 20 minutes.
Do not let boil.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fully cook sausage; drain well. Combine sausage, onion, cheese and flour.
Mix well.
Spread in unbaked pie crust shell.

title: an old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Work the butter to a cream; add the flour, the sugar, the raisins, the candied peel and the chopped almonds.
Mix them well together.
Whisk the eggs and add them to the dry ingredients. Beat the whole for about 10 minutes.
Pour the batter into a greased, paper-lined cake pan and bake in a preheated oven for 1 hour or until cake is done at 350°.
Makes 2 nice sized cakes.

title: turkey or chicken stew
directions: Bring to boil broth and water.
Add chicken, celery and onion. Cook slow about 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Add tomatoes, okra and seasonings.
Mix well.
Cook about another 30 minutes.
Add cooked egg noodles.
Cook about 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Feeds a crowd.
Good with cornbread.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions, using 9 x 13-inch pan. Punch holes in baked cake with handle of wooden spoon while cake is still warm.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, pina colada mix and pineapple together.
Pour over warm cake.
When chilled, frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine the sugar and flour.
Heat butter with cocoa and cola to a boiling point.
Pour this over the flour and sugar mixture; mix thoroughly.
In another bowl, add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla, salt and marshmallows.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil noodles, drain and cool.
Then add both soups; mix well. Add onion, milk, chicken and butter; mix well.

title: hot dogs n' crescents
directions: Heat oven to 425.
Grease cookie sheet.
Stir Bisquick, milk, and mustard until soft dough forms.
Beat for 30 seconds.
Place dough on surface sprinkled with Bisquick.
Roll dough in Bisquick to coat.
Shape into a ball.
Knead 10 times.
Roll or pat dough into 13 inch circle.
Cut into 8 wedges.
Place about 1 tsp. pickle relish
and 1 cheese strip on each wedge about 1 inch from rounded edge.
Top with hot dog.
Roll up beginning at rounded edge. Place crescent with tips underneath on the cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Combine with prepare sauce and beef.
Place in 4-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for a crowd!

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and lemon juice.
Let mixture stand overnight.
Mix in large pot the strawberry jello and water. Bring to a boil.
Add rhubarb sugar mixture.
Heat until boiling and boil until rhubarb is soft (about 3 or 4 minutes or longer). Pour into containers and freeze.

title: play dough
directions: Put a few drops of food coloring in a cup of water; add vegetable oil.
Stir and cook over medium heat until thick.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and oil; pour over salad.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Tie allspice, cinnamon and cloves in cheesecloth bag.
Heat cider with brown sugar; add spice bag.
Let simmer over low heat for 10 minutes or until cider is spicy enough to suit taste. Remove spice bag.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until
frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat until
lemon
colored.
Stir
in
zucchini and flour with cinnamon, baking
powder,
soda and salt.
Add nuts, pour into 2 greased and
floured
x 5-inch pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven 1 hour or until tests done.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Great dip for raw carrots, celery and cauliflower as well as the usual chips and crackers.

title: hazruquive(hopi hominy, bean sprout, corncob stew)
directions: Place hominy in a large saucepan with enough water to cover. Bring to boil on high and add stock, salt and pepper.
Return to boil, reduce the heat to medium and cook 10 minutes.
Add corn and cook for 10 minutes or until tender.
Add sprouts; reduce to low and simmer until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sloppy joe
directions: Brown meat and add all ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat berries with a mixer.
Sift and mix dry ingredients and add to strawberries with eggs, nuts and oil.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
If you are using small loaf pans, only bake for about 40 to 45 minutes.
(I can usually get 5 or 6 loaves.)

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all together with mayonnaise, salt, pepper and Old Bay seasonings.

title: super rolls
directions: Melt shortening in milk over low heat.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt and cold water.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
When milk mixture is lukewarm, mix these 3 together.
Add flour, but do it gradually.
Dough should drop off spoon (not too stiff).
Cover and place in icebox overnight.
Place on floured bread board. Work dough and cut in small pieces.
Place in cupcake pans that have been greased.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until nicely browned.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Blend remaining ingredients; add dry mixture.
Heat a small amount of oil in a large heavy skillet or an 11 x 8-inch pan.
Add cornbread batter. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook
pasta;
drain,
cool and set aside.
Mix together the mayonnaise,
vinegar
and
mustard.
Blend in blender the parsley and garlic.
Mix both mixtures together and set aside. Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Combine all mixtures together and chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: fried chicken batter
directions: Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: fresh apple bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cover with sifted powdered sugar. Cut into bars or can be baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour. Very good served with Cool Whip on top, if you like.

title: lemon-cheese filling
directions: Mix all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
I usually beat my eggs good with a portable mixer.
Ice cake when cool.
Good when Sour Cream Pound Cake is used for layers.

title: french bean casserole
directions: Saute in 1 stick of margarine the onion, celery and green pepper (optional).
Mix with remaining ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish and top with more crushed crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tortillas party pinwheels
directions: Mix the cream cheese and dressing mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up and wrap; chill for 2 hours or longer.
Cut off ends.
Cut in 1-inch slices.
Arrange on platter.
Very good.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel, core and slice tomatoes.
Chop onions and peppers.
Put into large kettle.
Add other ingredients. Stirring frequently, cook on top of stove until the consistency of ketchup (about 4 hours).
Pack in jars while hot and seal.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to directions on package (you can just steam the broccoli, if you prefer).
Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add Cheddar cheese soup and cream soup.
Blend together until smooth.
Add cooked or steamed broccoli and croutons; mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Top with approximately 1 cup of bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown and bubbly.
Bake approximately 30 minutes.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a casserole.
Pour fruit in butter.
Pour mixture of flour and milk into fruit and butter.
Sprinkle sugar over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pasta and beans with rosemary
directions: If using dried beans, rinse them and pick them over.
Then rehydrate and cook.
Drain and set aside.
If using canned beans, drain, rinse and drain.
Set aside.

title: mother's slaw
directions: Slice the onion over 1/2 head cabbage.
Slice remaining cabbage. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on this. Set aside.
Mix and heat to a boil the vinegar, oil, celery seed, mustard and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Pour this mixture over cabbage and onion.
Let stand at least 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: baba au rhum
directions: Cool scalded milk to lukewarm.
Add crumbled yeast, 1/2 cup flour and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 1 hour.
Cream butter, gradually adding 6 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until light.
Add salt, lemon rind, eggs, 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast mixture.
Beat well, about 15 minutes.
Half fill special molds which are well buttered both on the bottom and on the sides.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Cook 40 minutes in a moderate oven (350°).

title: peanut butter rice krispie bars
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: tuna dip
directions: Drain tuna; mix tuna, cream cheese, Texas Pete and onions until smooth.
Add Texas Pete to taste.
Serve with crackers.

title: taco salad
directions: In large bowl of mixer, pour boiling water over gelatin; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add cold water, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Freeze about 25 minutes or until firm about 1-inch from side of bowl but still soft in center.
Beat at medium speed until fluffy.
Fold in diced apples, walnuts and celery.
Turn into a 1-quart mold or individual molds.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
Unmold on plate.
Garnish with greens and apple slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: coney or pasta topping
directions: Fry slowly until lightly browned, the first 3 ingredients. Add tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Add salt, if desired and sugar (this brings out the flavors better, not just for a sweetener). Be sure to drain mushrooms.
After all this is added to the original 3 or 4 ingredients, boil slowly for 10 to 15 minutes or until of desired consistency.

title: lemon-mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine 3 tablespoons lemon juice, mustard and lime juice.
Rinse and dry chicken; brush chicken with mustard mixture, coating well.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine crumbs and seasonings.
Roll chicken in crumb mixture; press all crumbs into chicken.
Place chicken, meaty side down, in dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
Turn; bake 20 minutes longer or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mom's date-nut pudding
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix dates and nuts with flour until well coated.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; add sugar, then add date-flour mixture and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: best black beans
directions: Saute sausage and onion. Add beans, chicken broth and pepper. Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Mix well and drop on greased baking sheets. Refrigerate for several hours.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Form into rolls; chill and slice.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° to 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: veal rocco
directions: Dust veal medallions in flour.
Slice onion and pepper in thin strips about 1 1/2-inch.
Dice tomatoes.
Saute veal medallions in butter with onion and pepper until veal is browned, turning as needed.
Add sun dried tomatoes and artichoke hearts.
Drain butter from pan.
Simmer wine.
Remove veal from pan.
Simmer wine with the vegetables until sauce reduces to semi-thick consistency. You may substitute chicken breast for the veal.

title: dilly chicken sandwiches
directions: Pound chicken to flatten evenly; set aside. In a skillet, melt 3 tablespoons of butter; add garlic and 1/2 teaspoon dill. Add chicken; cook until juices run clear. Remove and keep warm. Spread both sides of bread with remaining butter. In a skillet or griddle, grill bread on both sides until golden brown. In small bowl, combine cream cheese, lemon juice and remaining dill; spread on one side of grilled bread. Place lettuce, chicken and tomato on 4 slices of bread; top with remaining bread. Makes 4 servings.

title: croatian corn bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients first.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 425° until top is nice and brown.

title: night before french toast
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch deep baking pan.
Cut the bread into 1-inch thick slices and arrange in a single layer in the pan.
In a large bowl, combine the eggs, salt, milk, sugar and vanilla, beating with an electric mixer.
Pour the mixture over the bread. Sprinkle with the cinnamon and allspice.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 6 to 24 hours.
Dot with butter and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, until the bread is lightly browned.
Remove from the oven and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve with warm maple syrup or confectioners sugar, yogurt or fresh fruit.
Serves 4.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Brown skinned sausage.
Add onions and brown.
Add broth, tomatoes and other ingredients.
Simmer for several hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease a baking dish with part of oil.
Dip asparagus in cream (reserve rest of cream).
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place asparagus in a baking dish.
Pour cream over.
Sprinkle diced Mozzarella cheese and the rest of the oil over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add 1 cup warm water, sugar and potato flakes.
Mix and store in refrigerator.
Put starter in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.

title: family favorite roast and gravy
directions: Do not add any salt.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix sugar, egg, flour, vinegar and juice from pineapple in a saucepan over low heat; stir until thick.
Chill.
Mix with Cool Whip, pineapple chunks, apples, peanuts and marshmallows.
Serve.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown ribs, arrange in shallow roasting pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan; cook 5 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture on ribs.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until ribs are done.
Brush barbecue sauce on ribs occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate bark cookies
directions: Melt the chocolate bark and peanut butter in double boiler. In a large bowl, combine the Rice Krispies, nuts and marshmallows. Pour hot mixture over the dry mixture and stir to coat.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk.
Dissolve yeast in water and then add to mixture. Cover bowl and refrigerate.
The mixture can be used for several days.
Roll on floured board 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick, cut with biscuit cutter and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 315°.
Use glass pans.
These amounts are for an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Double for a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Bake at 315° around 1 hour or a little less, will brown some.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant.
Cook with onions until tender.
Mash. Add oleo, milk, eggs, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup bread crumbs.
Put half into buttered casserole.
Add cheese.
Repeat layer of eggplant; top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix diced beef, cheeses and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Add kraut (drained).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with rye bread.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients together in a large bowl.
If you want to, you can save a little of the cheese out to sprinkle on top of the salad.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Reduce heat and stir in the oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 30 minutes in 325° oven.
Cover with crushed potato chips and serve.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Form into balls.
Put toothpicks in and freeze.
Melt chocolate and wax and dip balls.
Put balls on wax paper and let cool.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon and mix with remaining ingredients, adding about 1/4 cup of the liquid back into the mixture.
Mix well into patties.
Fry until brown in about 2 tablespoons of cooking oil.

title: fun cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar until fluffy; beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend flour mixture in slowly. Stir in M&M's and nuts.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix cake ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and place in 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Stir together soup and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and beaten egg to soup and cheese mixture.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with remaining grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 45 minutes until lightly browned.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter, then into crumb mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours (bone in) or 45 minutes to 1 hour (boneless).

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray. Brown, crumble and drain sausage. Press crescent rolls onto bottom of pan so that it stretches to edges. Cover dough with drained sausage. Top with hash browns and grated cheese. In a bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour this over crust. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Ingredients in brackets denote recipe halved.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk, soda, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Cook raisins in a little water until tender.
Mix flour and oatmeal, then add to shortening mixture.
Add raisins and water that raisins were cooked in.
Add 1 capful of vinegar.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This casserole tastes a lot like dressing so you can add chopped cooked chicken to the recipe before you bake it and serve in place of dressing.

title: sausage dip
directions: Crumble and brown sausage in skillet.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Cut cream cheese and put into the skillet.
Add tomatoes; warm until cream cheese is melted.
Add drained sausage. Serve with chips.
Use less tomatoes for milder dish.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour half of batter in sheet cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with butter and milk.

title: sherry's nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and season.
Drain off fat.
Put all ingredients together in crock-pot to melt.
Stir frequently. Serve with nacho chips.

title: cherries delight
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Fold in sour cream.
Break cake into small pieces.
Layer of cake on bottom, layer of pie filling, layer of pudding mixture and repeat. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli according to box instructions.
Melt Cheez Whiz in another pot and add cream of mushroom soup, then add cooked broccoli.
Mix together.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Take a medium-size pot.
Put cooking oil all around the bottom of the pot; turn stove on medium heat.
Put onion (chopped very fine) and bell pepper (chopped very fine) in pot.
Cook onion and bell pepper until they reduce in cooking oil.
Keep adding water until reduced, around 30 minutes.

title: indian relish
directions: Combine green tomatoes and salt and let stand overnight. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours.
Jar and seal.

title: chewy dunking snaps
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Then mix flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add to shortening mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip tops into sugar or decorating candies.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: apple cake(yields 1 cake)
directions: Cream together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add 4 chopped apples (approximately 2 cups).

title: taco dip
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients together and spread in bottom of a large dish.
Layer the remaining ingredients in the following order:
onions, olives, tomatoes and cheeses.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Keeps well for several days.
It's best when made a day ahead.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts generously with seasoned salt and paprika.
Arrange in 10-inch ceramic skillet.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave oven on High about 10 minutes.
Combine bouillon cube, water, onion, curry powder and Sauterne.
Pour over chicken.
Cook in microwave oven on High 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn chicken every 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms 3 minutes before cooking time ends.

title: heavenly cherry cake(makes 15 servings)
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions, except substitute 1 cup milk for water.

Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bring pineapple and sugar to boil and then simmer 3 minutes; cool. When cake has cooled, punch holes in the top and gradually pour pineapple mixture over top.
With electric mixer, beat pudding mix and 1 1/4 c. milk; add cream cheese, beating well.
Spread pudding over cake; top with bananas, 1/2 cup coconut and 1/4 cup cherries. Spread whipped topping over top.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut, cherries and pecans.
Chill.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Add egg, pineapple juice and vinegar.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Cool.
Stir in pineapple and apples.
Stir in nuts and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Grease
and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cake mix, oil, eggs and water.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix 1 cup of cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk in bowl.
Punch holes
in cake
while
hot.
Pour mixture on cake.
Let cool. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured pan (tube).
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
A raw streak should be in the top of cake when done.

title: bourbon grilled salmon
directions: Rinse the salmon filets and place them on a covered, paper towel-lined plate in the refrigerator. Prepare the marinade by placing all the ingredients, except the butter and half of the brown sugar, in the blender of food processor and mix well. Reserve 1/2 cup of the marinade and set aside.

Lay the salmon out in a nonmetallic casserole dish and pour the marinade evenly over all the filets. Cover and place in the refrigerator for a minimum of 4 hours (overnight is fine). Combine the butter and the remaining marinade in a small saucepan; warm over medium heat. When the butter has melted, whisk in the brown sugar, stirring vigorously for 3 minutes to complete the glaze and reserve. Grill the fish over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes per side. Baste liberally with the glaze just before serving. This dish holds well in a warm oven.

title: chili
directions: Peel potatoes; dice potatoes.
Put in kettle and add 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook until almost done.
Don't pour off potato water.
Fry meat with onions, salt and pepper.
Add to the potatoes.
Also add kidney beans, tomato soup and catsup.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 11 casserole dish with Pam.
Slice potatoes and layer with pork chops.
Top with soups and cover with foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken between wax paper and flatten with rolling pin. Sprinkle parsley and Italian seasoning over chicken.
Place ham and cheese slices on chicken breast.
Roll up from small end and stick a toothpick in to hold. Mix mayonnaise and water, brush on chicken.
Mix bread crumbs and rest of Italian seasoning.
Roll chicken in breadcrumbs and place in baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: apple slices
directions: Mix with fork.
Put 2/3 in jelly roll pan.
Press into pan. Save 1/3 to crumble on top.
Add a little more flour and sugar to this, about 2 tablespoons flour and 1 teaspoon sugar.

title: colette's taco pie
directions: Line a pie pan with the opened crescent roll dough.
Crunch 2 cups of Frito chips; set aside.
Brown the ground meat and add seasoning mix, olives, chilies and 1 canful of water.
Cook until liquid is absorbed.
Layer over the crescent crust in this order: 1 cup chip crumbs, meat mixture, sour cream and grated cheese.
Pat remaining cup of chip crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until crust is browned.
Serve with chopped lettuce, chopped tomatoes, avocado or guacamole and salsa.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter over medium heat until tender (about 10 minutes).
Add flour and cornstarch and stir until blended.
Slowly add broth and milk, then cheese.
Cook over slow heat until cheese is melted.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: roast turkey
directions: Clean turkey of feathers and fat.
Stuff cubed onion, sliced lemon and sage into body cavity.
Brush outside with butter and season with salt.
Bake at 325° for approximately 4 hours.
Baste often.
When turkey turns golden brown, cover with foil tent.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients (may use egg substitute for eggs). Place bread cubes in buttered glass 2-quart casserole baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/3 cup raisins, if desired.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Place dish in pan of hot water in middle of oven.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: black-eyed pea soup with smoked turkey
directions: Pour 1 quart hot water over the peas; cover and soak for 1 hour.
After soaking, rinse at least twice in fresh cold water.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake(this is very attractive)
directions: Bake cake in 2 round cake pans according to package instructions.
Cool and refrigerate to chill.
Then cut 1 layer into small pieces and place in a punch bowl.
Mix pudding according to package.
Spread half the pudding on top.
Add half the strawberries.
Layer half the pineapple on top and add 1 sliced banana.
Spread half of whipped topping on top.
Repeat with other cake layer, ending with whipped topping.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix prepared instant mashed potatoes (can be warm or cold, but must be instant potatoes) with eggs, flour and cream cheese.
Beat well.
Add onion.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Put onion rings on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Mash and add remaining ingredients. Put in casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350° covered.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all into 13 x 9-inch pan, starting with pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the pretzels, sugar and melted margarine together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and whipped topping.
Spread over the cooled pretzel crust.
Chill.
Mix gelatin and boiling water. Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir until soft set.
Add to crust and cream cheese mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: brown sugar refrigerator cookies(makes 6 dozen)
directions: In a mixer bowl, cream eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla. Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Blend well; stir in nuts.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half into a log 2 inches in diameter in waxed paper.
Twist ends shut. Refrigerate until firm, at least overnight.
Cut rolls into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Set slices 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden crisp.
Serve hot or remove while hot onto rack to cool.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, 1 cup sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in pineapple, soda, salt and flour.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased sheet.
Sprinkle with mixture of nutmeg and 1 tablespoon sugar. Bake for 10 minutes in 375° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use buttered and floured large bread pan.
(Recipe can be doubled or tripled.)

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all ingredients and mix together.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Heat juices from pineapple and cherries.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Heat butter and oil in skillet.
Add chicken.
Cook, uncovered over medium heat for 5 to 6 minutes on each side.
Top with cheese; sprinkle with parsley.
Cook, covered, for 3 minutes, cheese is semi-melted.
Remove chicken.
Keep warm.
Add garlic to drippings in skillet and saute for 30 seconds.
Stir in wine.
Continue stirring and scraping up brown bits which cling to bottom.
Stir in cream and cook sauce until thickens, about 3 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour sauce over chicken.

title: creamy pasta bean salad
directions: Blend all dressing ingredients using wire whisk.
Cook pasta and drain.
Combine pasta and other salad ingredients.
Pour dressing over salad; toss gently.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Add garlic salt, pizza sauce, tomato sauce and water.
Pour sauce mixture over macaroni.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Melt margarine and mix with vanilla wafers.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan to make crust.
Stir together Cool Whip and sour cream; spread over crust.
Clean and slice strawberries.
Mix berries with glaze.
Spread over the Cool Whip and sour cream mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: hearty red bean soup
directions: Cook beans in stock with meat for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients except potato.
Simmer 30 minutes, add potato, simmer until done.

title: spicy fried chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for 2 hours in mixture of spices.
Fry chicken pieces in the hot oil until golden brown. If the chicken begins to stick to the pan, add about 1/8 cup water. Best served immediately.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix by hand.
Dump into greased bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: beautiful red and green salad
directions: Sprinkle bed of greens with walnuts, cheese, chopped green onions and chopped or cubed beets. Drizzle dressing.

title: larry's double corn biscuits
directions: Mix first 5 dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine and oil until crumbly.
Stir in onion, milk and corn to form dough.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for about 12 minutes or until slightly browned.
Serves 16.
Can be frozen and reheated in microwave for about 38 seconds.

title: white crackers
directions: Spread peanut butter between Ritz crackers.
Dip in white chocolate.
Let cool.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Mix chicken and vegetables in dish.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper; pour over chicken mixture.
Combine flour, milk and butter; stir until smooth.
Pour over mixture in a baking dish. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly brown.
Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine all ingredients into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O using all hot water in glass oblong pan.
Add crushed pineapple.
Stir well; add blueberry pie filling.
Put in refrigerator at least three hours.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread over Jell-O after it's set.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over top if desired.

title: roast pork with oranges
directions: Rub pork with sage, salt and pepper.
Put on rack in shallow roasting pan and add the water.
Roast, uncovered, in preheated slow oven (325°) for 2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 170°.
About 45 minutes before meat is done, remove from oven and pour off fat, leaving pan juices.
Spread jelly over meat and sprinkle with orange rind.
Pour orange juice and sherry over meat.
Finish roasting.
Five minutes before meat is done, add oranges to heat slightly.
Put meat on a platter.

title: barbecued string beans
directions: Brown bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Add next five ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Let stand for at least 1 hour.
Drain beans and add to mixture.
Reheat and serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish in the order listed. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly (approximately 20 minutes).

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients, except poppy seed, as you would any cake mix. Blend in poppy seed last.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream the soda dissolved in buttermilk, sugar, eggs and butter.
I also use 1 teaspoon vanilla in mine.
Place 1 cup flour in a large bowl. Add cut up dates and stir to coat all pieces. Add rest of flour and coconut to cream mixture.
Grease pan very good or spray with Pam.
May also be floured lightly.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Skin chicken breasts and remove from the bone.
Brown chicken in olive oil.
Add 1/2 cup white cooking wine; immediately add fresh vegetables to pan.
Cook in wok or cast-iron frypan over high heat or nonstick frypan, until vegetables are heated (10 to 12 minutes).
Do not over cook vegetables.
Add teriyaki sauce and soy sauce.
Serve with cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 6 persons.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can onion rings.
Pour into greased 1 qt.
casserole.

title: red cinnamon pickles
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers.
Soak 24 hours in 1 cup lime to a gallon of water.
Drain, rinse and soak in ice water for 3 hours. Mix 1 cup vinegar, food coloring and alum with enough water to cover cucumbers.
Pour mixture over cucumbers in pot and simmer 2 hours.
Pour off liquid.
In another pot, boil 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, sugar, cinnamon sticks and candy until candy melts. Pour over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours.
Pour off liquid into another pot and bring to boiling again.
Pack cucumbers in warm jars and seal.
Process in water bath for 10 minutes.
These are nice at Christmas.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Finely chop carrots, celery and onion.
Use the amount to your liking.
Dice the hard-boiled eggs.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Beat well all ingredients and spread on cake when cooled.

title: ma's fudge
directions: Mix and cook first 5 ingredients.
Cook until a drop of mixture forms a hard ball in glass of cold water or until mixture stays on top of cold water.
Take mixture off stove; quickly add vanilla, peanut butter and nuts if desired.
Pour immediately into buttered loaf pan and let cool.
Cut in squares.
Do not cut until totally cooled.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Tastes best if mixed ahead and refrigerated.

title: fudge layer crumb bars
directions: Beat cake mix, margarine, egg and chopped nuts together until crumbly.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups for topping.
Press rest of mix into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until moist.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes.

title: mississippi rice salad
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: peanut butter crackles
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix margarine and peanut butter.
Stir in sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixed.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven; quickly press chocolate chips into cookie top.
Makes 48 (2-inch) cookies.

title: bluegrass pie
directions: Beat together sugar, corn syrup, eggs and vanilla.
Melt margarine.
Cool and beat into egg mixture.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips and pour into pie shell.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs, beating well.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Then add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat into pizza pan.
Bring only short way up side.
Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool completely.

title: banana pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, combine sugar, flour and salt. Blend with dry ingredients the milk; stirring constantly, add egg yolks.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes, then add vanilla.
Spread a small amount of custard on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with layer of wafers and layer of bananas.
Cover with 1/2 of custard; repeat for 3 layers.

title: autumn pudding(sweet potato casserole)
directions: Mix the ingredients for casserole and place in a 2-1/2 quart dish.

title: rich chocolate almond bars
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Spread dough on greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Prick dough and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over dough.
Place in oven again and bake for 3 minutes until chocolate melts.
Remove from oven.
Using spatula, spread melted chocolate over dough evenly.
Beat eggs with sugar; stir in vanilla and melted butter. Pour over cake, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool cake and cut into squares. Makes approximately 24 to 32 squares.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and place in enough boiling, salted water to cover. With a fork in one hand and knife in the other, keep cutting off cabbage leaves as they become soft. Trim thick center vein off each cabbage leaf. Brown onion in shortening. Add meat, seasonings and rice; mix well. Place a tablespoon of this filling on each cabbage leaf and roll. Tuck ends in. Place in a pot and layer each layer with sauerkraut. Add tomato juice and enough water to cover rolls. Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours or until rice tests done. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix until smooth the oil, orange juice, eggs, lime jello, and lemon cake mix.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 15 pan.
Bake at 325° for 25-30 minutes or until done when tested.
Prick with fork all over while hot.
Combine lime juice with 5-6 tablespoons of 4x sugar.
Pour over cake and cool.

title: cinnamon cream cheese rolls
directions: Place ingredients in the pan of the bread machine in the order recommended by the manufacturer.
Select dough cycle; press Start.
After the dough has doubled in size, turn it out onto a lightly floured surface; cover and let rest for 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add to Ragu sauce and heat in saucepan on low.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: red cabbage sweet-sour
directions: Chop cabbage.
Brown bacon in skillet and pour off excess fat. Add to bacon bits the cabbage, onion and apples.
Combine salt, pepper, sugar and 1/4 cup water and pour over cabbage.
Mix well with fork.
Cook over moderately high heat for 10 minutes or until cabbage and apples are tender.
(Add more water if needed to keep from burning.)
Add vinegar and mix well.
If thickening is desired, mix cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Cook an additional minute or 2 until mixture comes to boiling point.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter.
Add water and simmer until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly about 40 minutes, stirring frequently to prevent burning.
Place in jars and keep refrigerated.
If sauce is not used within several days, freeze the sauce.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Combine and
melt
together Eagle Brand condensed milk, chocolate chips and
margarine.
Mix
together in a large bowl miniature
marshmallows
and
salted
peanuts.
Pour
melted mixture over marshmallow
and
nut mixture.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan
and
chill two hours.
Once mix is chilled it may be removed from refrigerator and left out indefinitely.

title: baked chicken and dressing
directions: Melt margarine; add Worcestershire sauce.
Place chicken pieces flat in baking pan.
Sprinkle dressing and parsley over chicken. Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until done.
Cover with foil while baking.
Baste halfway through. If needed, add water.
(I usually rinse my butter and saucepan out with a little water and add to the corners of the pan.

title: angel food delight
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.
May use some strawberries to garnish.

title: green bean deluxe
directions: Combine first four ingredients; add beans.
Turn into large casserole.
Sprinkle with onion rings and top with grated cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook broccoli 8 minutes in microwave.
Mix together.
Cook in crock-pot until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
When beef is almost brown, add flour, salt and pepper.
Turn off heat and stir to coat beef.
Put in crock-pot.
Add beef broth to skillet and stir to loosen flour. Add vegetables to crock-pot and pour beef over them.
Cook 12 to 14 hours on low heat.

title: "comforts" for cozy times(quick and easy)
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add milk.
Beat flour and baking powder into mix.
Drop by very small teaspoonfuls in hot deep fat.
They roll over and are ready for cinnamon sugar.

title: brisket(melt in your mouth good!)
directions: Sprinkle brisket with salt, pepper and garlic. Put in baking pan fat side up (trim off excess fat) Cover with onions, celery and chile sauce.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.

title: beef stuffing rouladens
directions: Combine contents of vegetable seasoning packet, water, apple juice and butter.
Stir until butter is melted.
Stir in stuffing crumbs.
Place 1/4 cup stuffing on each steak and roll up.
Place Rouladens in baking dish, seam side down around the edges of the dish.
Place remaining stuffing in the middle of the dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with mushroom sauce if desired.
(A rouladen is something which is rolled up.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add other ingredients.
Roll, cut and bake on lightly greased baking sheet at 325° until lightly brown.

title: crazy pudding
directions: Put in a baking pan.

title: amish cole slaw
directions: Stir ingredients together and let stand until it draws its own juice.

title: majorettes brownies
directions: Beat eggs for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and light brown sugar. Blend together, then mix into eggs the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: japanese cabbage
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter for about 5 minutes.
Add cabbage and a little salt and pepper.
No water.
Put lid on pot and cook about 5 minutes or until done; can stir one time.

title: over easy chocolate cake
directions: Melt butter in cake pan. Combine coconut, sugar, water and nuts.
Smooth into bottom of pan.
Prepare cake by box directions and pour over mixture in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Turn out in 5 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Break bread into pieces in large bowl; cover bread with water and soak well.
Then squeeze out water until bread is slightly moist.
In a bowl, mix cheese, eggs, pepper, salt, garlic, parsley and drained bread.
Add hamburger and mix well.
Roll in 2-inch balls and place in flat pans, side by side.
Bake in a preheated oven at 450° until golden brown or until meat ball springs back when you press on top of it, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 150 meat balls.
Freezes well.

title: texas cobbler
directions: Spray or grease 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Glass is best.
Mix pineapple and pie mix.
Spread evenly in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle coconut over 1st layer.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over coconut layer. Melt oleo and drizzle evenly over cake mix, making sure all mix is covered.
Cook approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mary's chili
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except masa harina, in a large cooking pot.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Mix masa harina in warm water and add to the chili toward the end of the cooking time.
Let chili simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add red pepper, if desired.

title: salisbury steak(microwave)
directions: Set power select at Medium-high.
Combine ground beef, 1/4 soup, 1/2 mushrooms (chopped), egg, 1/4 cup milk, bread crumbs, onion and pepper.
Shape into 6 patties and arrange in oblong baking dish.
Heat, covered with wax paper, 13 to 14 minutes, turning patties over* and rearranging once.
Drain and let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, in small glass bowl, combine remaining soup, mushrooms and milk; heat 2 to 3 minutes, stirring once.
Pour sauce over patties and garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pecan pound cake
directions: Combine butter and Crisco.
Mix well.
Add sugar and mix at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: just for kids valentine party cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; with grown-up help.
Place paper liners in 24 muffin cups.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake and cool cupcakes following package directions.
Frost each cupcake and decorate with candies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Add cracker crumbs, half the grated cheese, milk and egg.
Stir until well blended.

title: freezer cold slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and top with salt.
Boil 1 minute the sugar, vinegar and water.
Shred carrot and mix with cabbage.
Pour sugar mixture over cabbage and carrot when mixture is almost cool. Place in freezer containers and freeze.
Thaw for 1 hour before using.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix ingredients in food processor or electric mixer.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix together liquids in punch bowl.
Add a few drops of red food coloring if desired.
Add 1/2 gallon of vanilla ice cream to float on top and melt.

title: creamy tomato pork (or chicken)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil. Add the chicken stock, basil, salt and pepper; simmer. Add the pork chops and cook until done. Add the cream and tomato paste; heat through. Serve over rice or pasta.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill a 9-inch plate with apples (about 1/3 full).
Sprinkle with a tablespoon of sugar and cinnamon.
Mix balance of ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand.
Combine sugar, salt, shortening and boiling water; stir until shortening is melted and cool to warm.
Stir in yeast.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, until soft dough is formed.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook shrimp for 5 minutes in boiling water. Drain. Peel and devein. In large bowl mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve with your favorite meal.

title: vanilla cream frosting
directions: Blend butter, vanilla and salt; add 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Add hot cream and remaining sugar alternately in small amounts, beating after each addition.
Add only enough cream to make frosting soft enough to spread.
Will cover sides and top of 1 (10 x 10-inch) cake.

title: sausage ring and scrambled eggs
directions: Beat together 2 eggs and 1/2 cup milk.
Stir in cracker crumbs, apple, onion and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; add sausage.
Mix well. Firmly pat meat mixture into 6 1/2-cup ring mold.
Carefully unmold sausage ring onto a rack in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Transfer to platter.
Keep warm.
In a 3-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Blend flour.
Add remaining cup milk all at once.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Beat together the remaining 10 eggs, the cheese, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; stir into sauce.
Cook until eggs are firm.
Spoon eggs into sausage ring.
Serves 12.

title: rum wassail
directions: Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Combine sugar and juices in a 2-gallon container with spices and simmer for 30 minutes. Remove spice bag and add rum just before serving.
Serves 30.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Dust pork chops on both sides with flour. In a lightly greased skillet, saute pork chops on each side until golden brown. Remove and keep warm. Drain excess fat from skillet, if necessary, and saute onion until tender. Add tomatoes, green pepper, salt, pepper and worcestershire sauce. Return pork chops to tomato mixture and simmer, covered, 1 hour or until tender. Meanwhile, cook rice. Arrange pork chops on a heated platter. Cover chops with hot fluffy rice; then pour the tomato sauce over all. Serves 6.

title: no fuss potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes and place in a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with onions and pour soup over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover with sliced cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: tex-mex chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together soup, water, chili powder and cumin.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add all remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup of each cheese.
Spoon into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Can be refrigerated overnight, bake uncovered 45 minutes.
Top with sour cream and salsa, if desired.

title: wine jello salad
directions: Mix well in a bowl the gelatin and sugar.
Add boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Add juices and wine.
Mix, mold and chill.
Or pour onto flat pan for cutting shapes after chilling. Serves 6 to 8 as a dessert or 10 to 12 as an accompaniment for poultry.

title: frozen snickers bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze.
Cut into 8 bars and enjoy.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix and let stand for 3 minutes the warm water, yeast and sugar.
Mix well the oil, salt and flour.
Add to yeast mixture. Raise 45 minutes. Punch down. Pull off dough and form into patties.
Tear a hole in center like a doughnut.
Fry in hot grease at 375°, turning once, when first side is brown, then brown other side.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot with butter and choice of honey, powdered sugar or jams.
Serves about 6 to 8 people.

title: chocolate pound cake(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Sift flour and cocoa together. Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. To this mixture, add flour mixture and milk alternately a little at a time until all is used. Mix well. Bake in a greased and floured large tube pan for 1 hour and 40 minutes. Do not open oven during cooking.

title: squash supreme
directions: In large bowl, blend soup and sour cream; add carrots, onion and squash.
Melt butter and add stuffing mix.
Stir thoroughly. Spread half of mix on bottom of large casserole dish.
Pour squash mixture over and top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: bread sticks
directions: Slice buns two ways so that each bun makes four bread sticks. Brush each stick liberally with melted margarine to which some garlic powder has been added (to taste).
Sprinkle buttered sticks with celery salt, poultry seasoning and parsley flakes.
Place sticks on cookie sheet in low oven (200° to 250°).
Bake approximately 1 hour or until sticks are very dry and crisp. Allow to cool completely before placing in bags.
Can be frozen.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix crackers and butter.
Set aside.
Mix milk, mayonnaise and soup.
Pour over shredded cabbage.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Then add crackers on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until done.
Crackers will be brown on top.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Combine margarine, 1 egg and cake mix in a large bowl; mix well. Press mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. Set aside. Combine 2 eggs, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy. Spread topping over cake layer. Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool on wire rack. Cut into squares. Yield: about 2 doz. squares.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Rub salad bowl with a cut clove of garlic, then put the egg yolk, salt, mustard, pepper, paprika, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce in the bowl; blend thoroughly.
Add oil; blend again.
Add the greens and lettuce, torn into bite size chunks and tossed lightly.
A few spoonfuls of Roquefort cheese, crumbled, make this extra special.

title: john and stacy's hot potato salad
directions: Layer each: cubed boiled potatoes, sliced boiled eggs and chopped onion.
Pour mixture of Miracle Whip, sugar and mustard over the layered ingredients.
Fry bacon and crumble on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: 24 hour layer salad
directions: Layer, do not toss.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This makes quite a bit, so you need a large storage container.
Pour 1/2 cup of powder into cup and fill with water.
Goes great on ice cream.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Fry meat and onions.
Add tomatoes, simmer with carrots until almost done.
Add other vegetables and beans except cabbage.
Add 3 to 4 cups shredded cabbage.
Do not stir it in, just push under juice on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until cabbage is done.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Chop peppers.
Mix all ingredients except Certo and bring to a rolling boil; stir times one.
Remove from heat.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Add Certo and mix.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: texican casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Brown hamburger with onion; drain. Combine canned goods and mix with hamburger and onion.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions.
Spoon on top and spread evenly.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: friendship harvest loaf
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening and water. Beat for 1 minute with electric mixer.
Add applesauce and egg, then beat for 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Happy harvest!

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Great served over bed of lettuce or just with crackers.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Bake in a 9-inch pie plate or ovenproof dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly and golden brown.
Serve with Triscuits or toasted pita wedges.

title: busy day supper
directions: First thing, put large pan of water on to boil (salt water) and measure noodles.
Noodles measure the same dry or wet.

title: louisiana style baked shrimp
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over shrimp.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla. Pour into Pam sprayed pie pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Combine sour cream, 4 tablespoons sugar and vanilla. Pour over cooled pie. Bake 10 minutes. Chill.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Put saltines in blender on high until powdered.
Add minced parsley, onion and dill weed.
Blend again until powdered.
Pour into bowl.
Stir in onion salt, garlic salt, onion powder and garlic powder.
Place into container with tight fitting lid. Blend 1 tablespoon of dry mix with 1 cup mayo and 1 cup buttermilk.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and mix well. Drop from teaspoon 1-inch apart onto well-greased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and baking sheet at once.
Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs until foamy; add sugar.
Add oil, vanilla and salt.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add zucchini and flour and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Grate
rind
and
squeeze lemons.
Mix flour and sugar. Add beaten egg yolks and all other ingredients.
Cook over low heat until
thick.
Cool and
spread
between
layers of cake. This is good when used with Six Layer Cake.

title: cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and sour cream until smooth. Stir in Parmesan cheese and 1/2 cup dried beef. Chill cheese mix for 15 minutes. Shape into ball and roll in remaining beef. Chill at least 20 minutes or longer.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Cover ham hocks with water. Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat from bones.
Add meat, beans and rest of ingredients to stock.
Simmer covered for 2 hours. Stir occasionally.
Serve over hot rice.

title: banana orange frost
directions: Mix orange juice, milk and sherbet in blender. Add banana. Mix on high speed until smooth.
Serve.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing 2 cans water to each can of frozen juice. Chill.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 9 x 13-inch or 2 (8-inch) cakes.

title: mary's french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients, except vinegar, in blender.
Blend well. Turn to slow, open vent in lid and add vinegar very slowly.
Pour in bottle or jar and refrigerate.

title: easter spinach pie
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain and press out liquid.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
In a large skillet, in the hot oil, gently cook onion until transparent. Stir spinach, onions and ham into eggs.
Add Parmesan, Ricotta, salt and pepper.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° until crust is golden, about 40 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving.
This will be better if you bake it the day before serving and reheat it at a moderate oven temperature.

title: sofia's stew
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add orange zest.
Arrange onions around meat.
Stir broth, 1/2 of brandy and garlic and pour over the meat.
Cover and cook slowly for about 2 1/2 hours.
Do not stir. Add carrots, tucking them under the meat.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Gently stir in parsley, lemon peel and rest of brandy. Salt for taste.
Ladle into soup bowls.
Serve with hot French bread, a green salad and a good Burgundy.

title: cracklin' bread(original)
directions: Put salt in meal.
Put your pork rinds in.
(Do not crush the rinds too fine.
I use my rolling pin to crush the rinds.)
Add hot water to make up bread (use hands).
Make into pones and bake in a 375° oven.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Freeze until cold.

title: no crust custard pie
directions: Add sugar, nutmeg, flour and milk to slightly beaten eggs. Pour into a 9-inch pie pan which has been greased with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook for 12 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Lift lid off to thicken the last 4 hours.
Immediately fill jars; wipe jar rims and threads.
Cover quickly with flat lids.
Screw bands on tightly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender. Drain and mash. Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble. Saute onion in bacon drippings. Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 1/2 cups hot water with sugar and salt in large bowl.
Stir in thawed strawberries and set in refrigerator until slightly set.
Whip cream, then fold into Jell-O mix.
Tear angel food cake into pieces and make a layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan, using half of the pieces.
Pour half of the Jell-O mix on pieces. Make another layer with remaining cake and the remaining Jell-O mix.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Take eggs, sugar and shortening (soft but not melted); mix until creamed.
Add sifted flour a little at a time.
Alternate. Add a little of the milk until flour and milk have all been mixed. Add spices and jam in last.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in layer pans or a sheet pan.
Bake slowly to prevent burning.
When you stick your finger on the cake, it will pop up if it is done.

title: toffee candy
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and butter in pan and bring to a boil.
Cook to 285° to 300°.
Do not stir after boiling starts. Add nuts and spread on warm, buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Melt chocolate bits, one half at a time, with paraffin.
Spread on top of candy.
Cool, then on other side.
Cool, then break into pieces.

title: german beef birds
directions: Cut round steak into serving portions.
Wrap around sausage links.
Secure with a toothpick.
Brown.
Add 1 quart tomatoes, onion, caraway seed, salt and pepper.
Add liquid from can of sauerkraut.
Cook 45 minutes.
Add sauerkraut and simmer 30 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: blueberry lime bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs, buttermilk, oil and lime juice together with sugars.

title: lemon danish cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine cake mix, sour cream, apricot baby food, lemon juice, water, eggs, and poppy seed. Beat on low speed of electric mixer for about 1 minute or until well mixed. In a small bowl, combine the cream cheese and confectioners' sugar.
Mix well.
