Line muffin pans with paper cupcake liners. Spoon the batter into liners, filling about 1/2 full.
Drop a small dollop (about a teaspoon) of cream cheese mixture in center of each cupcake. Spoon about a tablespoon of batter over the top, covering the cream cheese.
This will make the liners about 3/4 full. Bake for about 20 minutes or until top will spring back when lightly touched.
The cupcakes will not be brown on top. Remove from muffin pans and cool on a rack. Drizzle the cooled cupcakes with the confectioners' sugar glaze. Makes 24 cupcakes.

title: best ever kosher dills
directions: Wash small cucumbers and pack into sterile jars with fresh dill, mustard seed, garlic clove and hot pepper.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips and sprinkle with paprika. Allow meat to stand while preparing other ingredients. Using a large skillet, brown meat in butter. Add garlic and broth. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in onions and green peppers; cover and cook for 15 minutes. Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce. Stir into meat mixture. Cook, stirring until clear and thickened, about 2 minutes. Serve over rice. Makes a great supper with a salad and crusty French bread.

title: cauliflower-broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces and steam until soft.
Saute onions, celery and mushrooms in margarine until soft. Combine cooked vegetables with soup, Monterey Jack and sharp cheeses and milk for moist consistency.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: graham gems
directions: Bring to boil 2 sticks butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Place graham crackers on cookie sheet. Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Sprinkle pecans all over graham crackers.
Place in 325° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: parmesan cheese bread
directions: Thaw bread dough and shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip balls into melted butter, then cheese/spice mixture.
Arrange side by side in Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 200°.
Shut off.
Let dough rise about 1 hour or until it reaches to the top of pan.
Remove and preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: real fudge cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise, curry, onions and artichoke hearts with marinade. Chill 2 hours.
Great for picnics and potlucks.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Cream together cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Combine the pudding mixture with cream cheese; mix well.
In layers, alternate cookies and filling.
Refrigerate.

title: corned beef hash quiche
directions: Bake pie shell 7 minutes at 450°.
Turn temperature to 325°. Crumble hash into baked pie shell and top with cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over top and bake 35 minutes or until set.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add berries slightly frozen (do not mash berries).
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread with sour cream.
Add remaining gelatin on top. Chill.
Pour more sour cream on top when firm.

title: orange bread
directions: Combine yeast and sugar.
Let stand a few minutes.
Heat orange juice to lukewarm and add to yeast.
Add remaining ingredients, except candied orange peel.
Beat well.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Knead in orange peel on well floured board.
Shape into a loaf and let rise until doubled in bulk, or until light.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.

title: chili mac
directions: Add macaroni and salt to boiling water; boil for 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water, then drain thoroughly.

title: mexican delight casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef and onion until beef is browned; drain fat.
Add Burrito Spices and tomatoes; mix well. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat; reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Combine hominy or corn and green chiles in separate bowl.
In 2-quart rectangular casserole dish, layer half of meat mixture, tortilla chips and hominy mixture.
Add 1/2 cut cheese.
Repeat layers (if using red and green chips alternate the colors with layers, looks very good), ending with 1/2 cup cheese.
Top with tomato sauce and remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake, uncovered, in 350 degree oven for 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve with a tossed green salad.
Teens love this meal!!!

title: tang pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in shells.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel, core and slice apples into a 9-inch pie pan or dish.
Coat apples with lemon juice.
Work like pastry with a pastry blender or with the fingertips:
flour, brown sugar, butter, salt and cinnamon.
Mixture must be lightly worked so that it does not become oily.
Spread crumbly mixture over the apples.
Bake for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix spices with boiling water; stir into sweet potatoes.
Add sugar, eggs, salt and butter; blend thoroughly.
Stir in milk; heat mixture over hot water for about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° until filling is set, about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with Whipped Orange Topping.

title: mandarin orange fruit salad(5 cup salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix lemonade and condensed milk in large bowl, then add Cool Whip. Mix very well. Pour in graham cracker crust, then refrigerate.

title: chicken piquant
directions: Place mushrooms in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken over mushrooms.
Combine cornstarch and water in small bowl, stirring until smooth.
Stir in olive oil, if desired; add wine, soy sauce, garlic, brown sugar and oregano. Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, or until chicken is done.
Serve with rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook the turkey, onion and garlic in large skillet until the turkey is no longer pink.
Drain fat.
Add vinegar, chili powder, oregano, cumin and red pepper, if desired.
Cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Add beans.
Remove from heat.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Soak 1 cup rolled oats,
1/2 cup crumbled crackers in 1 cup milk.
Add 2 beaten
eggs.
Add
meat,
onion
and celery. Add more cracker crumbs if
needed.
Form
into a loaf; spread catsup or barbecue sauce over the loaf before baking.

title: skillet beef and noodles
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water, salted, until just tender, about 8 minutes.
Drain and reserve.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon and flake.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Form into ball; roll in parsley flakes. Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with graham crackers.
Then mix pudding and milk together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Then pour over first layer of graham crackers.
Then layer with graham crackers. Melt chocolate and butter over boiling water, add sugar and water. Mix. Pour this over second layer of graham crackers.
Chill.

title: vegetable-cheese lasagna
directions: In skillet, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly; add mushrooms and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan, heat oil over medium heat; add onions and garlic and saute 1 to 2 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, 3/4 teaspoon salt, the oregano, basil, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and bay leaf; mix well.
Reduce heat to low, cover and let simmer, stirring occasionally for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaf.

title: poor man hamburger steak
directions: Mix hamburger with desired seasonings.
Make patties and roll in crushed corn flakes.
Cook patties in skillet.

title: brownie cheesecake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Mix next 3 ingredients in second bowl.
Press 3/4 of cake mixture into slightly greased cake pan.
Set aside remaining
1/4 of cake mixture. Pour cheesecake mixture into cake pan.
Sprinkle remaining cake mixture over cheesecake part.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: floating soda cracker bars
directions: Boil butter and sugar for 3 minutes.
Put foil in jelly roll pan and line with soda crackers.
Pour sugar/butter mixture on top; spread evenly.
Bake 5 minutes at 350° or until crackers "float."
Let cool a couple of minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
You can put this back in oven to melt.
Spread chocolate evenly.
Cut immediately.
Chopped nuts may be added.

title: penuche(candy)
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook to soft ball stage.
Cool to lukewarm and beat until creamy.
Pour on a greased plate and cut. Do not add walnuts until ready to pour.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Mix cheese thoroughly through dry Jell-O.
Mix in boiling water.
Drain fruit and save juice.
Add enough water to complete the 4 cups necessary for Jell-O.
Add fruit and 3/4 cup nut meats.

title: fiesta guacamole dip
directions: In small bowl, combine refried beans and chilies; spread on large serving plate.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning; spoon over bean mixture, spreading evenly.
In small bowl, mash avocados; stir in ReaLemon brand and salts.
Spoon evenly over sour cream mixture.
Cover; chill several hours.
Just before serving, garnish with cheese, tomatoes, green onions and olives. Serve with tortilla chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Combine ground beef, onions, green pepper and oil and brown in very large skillet.
Add tomatoes and corn; simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add chili powder, red pepper and salt.
Mix corn meal, milk and eggs together.
Add to first mixture.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and eggs.
This will be a stiff dough. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cookies will look fat and very soft but will fall and cool into delicious cookie.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Mix together dry mustard and vinegar; let stand overnight. Mix eggs, sugar and salt and blend with mustard mixture.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Let cool, then add Miracle Whip.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for about 2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: monkfish gratin
directions: Bake patty shells according to package directions; keep warm. Melt butter or margarine in a heavy 10-inch skillet.
Add crawfish; saute 5 minutes, stirring.
Remove crawfish with a slotted spoon; set aside.
Add mushrooms to skillet; saute until liquid is reduced to a glaze and mushrooms are caramelized.
Add stock or clam juice to deglaze pan, scraping up all browned bits from pan.
Cook over medium heat until liquid is reduced by 1/2. Add cream, seasonings and minced parsley.
Again, reduce by 1/2. Stir in green onions.
Return crawfish to sauce; cook just to heat through.
Serve in patty shells.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 to 12 servings.

title: jello pie
directions: Chill milk.
Line 3 pans with vanilla wafers.
Mix pineapple juice, Jell-O, sugar and eggs together.
Bring to a rolling boil. Set aside to cool.
Whip chilled milk and fold in cooked mixture until well blended.
Pour mixture into pans lined with wafers. Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: old fashion lasagne(kids' favorite)
directions: Place bacon, butter, garlic, onion and celery in saucepan; saute gently for 4 to 5 minutes.
Discard garlic.
Add beef, marjoram and parsley; simmer, stirring occasionally, until meat is browned.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste mixture.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Season to taste; cook for 10 to 15 minutes, or until sauce is thick.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While hot, punch holes in top of cake.
Mix sugar with pineapple and cook 5 minutes.
Pour pineapple and sugar mix over cake while hot.
Prepare vanilla pudding (not instant) and spread over pineapple.
Cover and refrigerate cake overnight.
When ready to serve, spread Cool Whip and coconut over the top.

title: mai-tai cocktail
directions: Fill a 14 ounce glass with shaved ice.
Stir in lime juice, syrup, curacao and light rum.
Drop in half of lime shell.
Float dark rum on top.
Garnish with a pineapple spear topped with sprig of mint.
(Float flower for a regal touch).
Serve with straw!

title: "no-name" dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press smoothly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then cool.
Cream the cheese and sugar; mix in 1 cup Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Whip pudding, milk and vanilla until thick and spread over cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Refrigerate; cut into squares and serve.
Freezes well.

title: supreme pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, drain fat.
Stir in water, celery and soup mix. Cover; cook over low heat 30 minutes or until chops are tender. Take skillet off heat.
Move chops to one side.
Mix together mushrooms and flour.
Stir flour-mushroom mixture, parsley flakes and evaporated milk into skillet.
Stir over low heat until steaming.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry and line the pastry with foil.
Add dried beans to weigh the bottom down and bake 30 minutes.
Remove the foil and beans.
Cook the bacon until crisp and remove from skillet.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon of fat remaining in skillet.
Cook the onion in the fat until transparent.
Crumble the bacon.
Sprinkle the bacon, onion and cheese over the inside of the baked shell.
Combine the eggs, cream, milk, nutmeg, salt and pepper and spread over onion-cheese mixture.
Bake the pie 45 minutes or until a knife inserted 1 inch from the pastry edge comes out clean.
Cut into wedges and serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: party pecans
directions: Melt margarine. Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt. Heat pecans in 250° oven in a shallow pan. Drizzle mixture over pecans and stir well. Return to oven. Toast 1 hour at 250°.

title: cocoa snowballs
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, add the cereal, coconut and nuts. Stir with a wooden spoon. Drop one ice cream scoop of ice cream at a time into mixture.
Roll the ball around until it is coated. Work quickly so the ice cream doesn't melt.
Place the ice cream balls on the cookie sheet.
Put them in the freezer until serving time.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until all sugar is melted (3 to 5 minutes).
Add orange juice and beat 2 minutes.
Mix baking powder with flour; add to mixture and beat 2 minutes.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in ungreased tube pan or square cake pan at 350°.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: overnight layered green salad
directions: Core lettuce and slice thinly.
Spread lettuce over the bottom of a wide 4-quart serving dish.
Slice green onions and sprinkle on top of lettuce.
Drain water chestnuts and slice; sprinkle over onions.
Slice red pepper and layer over the water chestnuts. Slice celery and sprinkle over the peppers.
Break apart frozen peas and spread over the celery.
Sprinkle with the salt, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder.
Finely chop and sprinkle bacon next, along with eggs (finely grated).
Cover the salad and chill for at least 4 hours or to 24 hours.
Just before serving, cut tomatoes in wedges and arrange around the top of the salad.
To serve, use a spoon and fork to lift out each serving.
Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: brilliant candy slices
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Blend in unbeaten egg, vanilla and sifted flour.
Stir candied fruit and pecan halves into mixture.
Shape into 2 small rolls.
Chill for at least 3 hours or overnight.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
These are nice at Christmastime.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Coarsely crumble corn bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer beans, tomatoes, bell pepper, green onions and bacon in order given.
Blend Miracle Whip and pickle juice until smooth. Add additional pickle juice if thinner consistency if desired. Spread over the vegetable and corn bread layers.
Serve chilled.

title: low-fat chicken pasta with sausage and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Cut chicken, tomatoes (once prepared) and sausage into bite-size pieces.
Prepare Fettucini Alfredo, using skim milk and no butter.
While fettucini is cooking, cook chicken, tomatoes and sausage in a skillet using Pam and water (no oil or butter).
Add chopped garlic to mixture while cooking.
When chicken is done, add all to completed Fettucini Alfredo.
Add Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: stir-fry pork
directions: Slice pork into thin strips about 2 inches long and 1/8-inch thick.
Combine broth, soy sauce, sherry and cornstarch; set aside.
Preheat stir-fry pan on high for 5 minutes.
Add oil and pork; stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes, or until pork is done.
Remove meat.
Add celery, onion, pea pods and ginger root to pan. Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add mushrooms; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add 1 tablespoon water.
Cover and allow to steam 1 minute, or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir pork into vegetables.
Add broth mixture; heat until mixture becomes thick and bubbly.
Serve over rice.

title: rice krispie squares
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil in large pan.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies or corn flakes, along with coconut (optional).
Mix until evenly coated.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: quickie cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in a pan.
Bring to a full rolling boil, approximately 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and let boil down for 1 minute.
Mix 1/2 cup peanut butter and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Add oatmeal gradually until thick enough to drop with a spoon onto wax paper or foil paper.
Amount of oatmeal depends on desired thickness.
Eat when cool.

title: plum pudding
directions: In a large bowl, sift flour, salt and spices.
Soak bread crumbs in hot milk for 10 minutes.
In separate bowl, beat sugar into well beaten egg yolks.
Add suet and soaked crumbs.
Stir into flour mixture.
Add fruits and brandy; mix well.
Put into a buttered mold (Bundt) pan, cover tightly and place into a pan of hot water.
Put into a 350° oven and steam cook for 3 1/2 hours. Serves 12.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light; beat in egg, vanilla and pumpkin.
Mix.
Mix other dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until firm to touch.
Remove from cookie sheet while still warm.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix ingredients and add bourbon.
Freeze to slush.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from chocolate pieces. In large mixing bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour; blend until smooth. Stir in small chocolate chips.
Mold scant tablespoon dough around each chocolate piece, covering completely.
Shape into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
(Do not wait until brown.)
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: four layer surprise
directions: Layer 1:
Mix flour, margarine and chopped pecans.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Several years ago, Ladies Home Journal had an interview with Katherine Hepburn, during which she served the magazine's reporter tea and brownies.
They were so spectacular that the reporter requested the recipe which was printed in the article.
When I saw that it included only 1/4 cup of flour, I knew it was a winner! Here it is, in Hepburn's own colorful language:

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Spread 1/2 stick oleo in a casserole dish; pour in batter.
Pour fruit with juice on top (1 to 2 cups).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix package stew mix with 3 cups of water into crock-pot.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook on low for 8 hours or cook on high for 4 1/2 hours.

title: peach praline pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; let stand for 15 minutes.
Combine flour and brown sugar; cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle 1/3 of flour mixture in bottom of pastry shell. Spoon in peaches and top with remaining flour mixture.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend with mixer until smooth. Pour batter into Bundt pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
(My oven takes about 42 minutes for it to be done correctly.)
Cool in Bundt pan on rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan onto serving plate and cool completely before covering.

title: chile verde(green chile and pork stew)
directions: Roast and peel the chiles, tear into strips and set aside. Removal of seeds and veins is optional in this recipe.
If canned chiles are used, rinse and tear into strips.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
With electric mixer, beat first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in peanuts.
Sprinkle pie shell with chips.
Pour in peanut mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Continue baking for 30 minutes or until fork inserted in center comes out clean.

title: funfetti cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl combine cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir by hand thoroughly until moistened.
Stir in decorator sprinkles from cake mix.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness with bottom of glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet and frost warm cookie. Immediately sprinkle with sprinkles from frosting.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: spicy cereal crunch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a heavy skillet.
Stir constantly over medium heat until boiling.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over cereals and nuts and stir to coat.
Spread on 2 buttered baking sheets.
When firm, break into pieces.

title: dad's (no egg) brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Pour into aluminum foil-lined and well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Lift foil package from pan.
Fold foil sides down.
Cool 20 minutes.
Cut into squares and transfer to cooling rack.
Sprinkle through sifter with sugar.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli if frozen; drain.
Line baking dish with broccoli.
Place chicken on broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Top with shredded cheese; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour; brown in hot fat.
Place in baking dish and set aside.
Brown onion in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in oven at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, soup, pepper and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: This recipe can be doubled.

title: quiche
directions: Optional: May also add 1/4 to 1/2 cup broccoli or 1/4 to 1/2 cup spinach or 1/4 to 1/2 cup ham.
Be creative.

title: two step coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Pour milk, eggs and vanilla into a blender.
Whip 30 seconds.
Add sugar, butter and biscuit mix.
Blend 1 minute.
Add the coconut and blend 5 seconds.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes until knife comes out clean.
We sprinkle coconut on top and brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Salt and pepper asparagus in a baking dish. Slowly melt cheese, milk and margarine until liquid. Add boiled eggs and mix.
Pour over asparagus.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake in preheated oven.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch.
Stir in meat, cheese, onions, peppers and salt.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: white salad
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and drained pineapple until the cream cheese is smooth.
Add to this mixture the Cool Whip.
Mix these ingredients.
Add the pecans and stir them in with a spoon.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat on stove until blended. Serve warm with apple slices.

title: layered macaroni shrimp salad
directions: In large bowl, layer greens, macaroni, 1 1/2 cups cheese substitute, tomatoes, shrimp, peas and cabbage.
Combine mayonnaise and bottled Italian dressing.
Pour over salad.
Top with remaining cheese substitute.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or the night before serving.
Toss to serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: swiss alpine pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Drain and chop broccoli. Layer broccoli, ham, cheese in pastry shell. Sprinkle onion over top. Stir milk into eggs; add seasonings and pour into pastry shell. Bake 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325 degrees and bake another 30 to 35 minutes. Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: seafood appetizer mold
directions: Heat the soup. Dissolve gelatin in water and add to the soup. Add softened cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour into an oiled mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold.
Serve with crackers.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together and add cooled raisins to this mixture. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge(no cooking)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in buttered plate until set good.
Cut into squares.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together	cream cheese, butter, sugar, and vanilla.
Mix together
pudding,	milk and Cool Whip, then mix both mixtures together.
Line
flowerpot	with
foil.
Crumble 1/2 package
of Oreo cookies and place in bottom of pot.
Pour in mixture and crumble rest of the cookies on top.

title: chocolate layered pie
directions: Mix together.
Put into the bottom and sides of 9 inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Cool.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleomargarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating slightly after each.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 325° in greased and floured rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) for 1 hour or until done when tested with a toothpick.

title: dutch carrots
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp; remove bacon.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until transparent.
Add carrots; season with salt and pepper.
Turn carrots into hot vegetable dish.
Garnish with bacon; serve immediately.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with 1/2 package Ritz cracker crumbs and bake for 20 minutes.

title: corn and okra jambalaya
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp; drain.
In same skillet, with the bacon drippings, saute okra and onions; do not brown.
Add tomatoes and corn; bring to a boil.
Simmer about 5 to 10 minutes.
Jambalaya must not be runny.
Serve over hot rice. Sprinkle bacon over top of each serving.

title: laurie davis' chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cool, bone and cut in small pieces. Cook spaghetti until tender and rinse in cold water.
Cook green pepper 5 minutes in a little chicken broth.
Put a layer of chicken in bottom of greased dish, then a bit of pepper, pimento, mushrooms and 1 can of soup.
Then add a layer of spaghetti; sprinkle with onion salt and layer of grated cheese.
Make second layer, putting chicken, pepper, pimentos, mushrooms and soup.
Put the second layer of spaghetti; sprinkle with onion salt and a thick layer of cheese (grated).
Top with bread or cracker crumbs and a few pieces of butter.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
This may be frozen. This may not be so simple, but it sure is good, especially for a family gathering or church supper.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine and
sugar.
Add
eggs
and flour.
Add flavoring.
Stir in preserves and nuts.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 275° for 2 hours.

title: broccoli and egg casserole
directions: Break half the bread in pieces and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with cheese, ham, veggies, etc.
(repeat twice).
Mix milk, eggs and seasonings nd pour over bread.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: fricadilloes
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into rolls about 2 1/2 inches long and 1 inch through.
Roll in the bread crumbs.
Bake 3/4 hour in a well-greased pan.
Keep covered the first 15 minutes.
After they are brown, put a little water in pan.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and remove stems.
Drain sprouts and chestnuts. Crumble the fried bacon.
Combine the spinach, bean sprouts, chestnuts, bacon and onion.
Heat in saucepan the salad oil, sugar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce and wine vinegar.
Do not boil until sugar melts.
Pour over greens.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes in 2 - 9 inch round cake pans that have been greased and floured.
Remove cakes from the oven and cool completely.
Slice each cake in half giving you 4 round cake pieces.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together well.
If mixture is
too thick, add small amount of water.
Drop by teaspoons into
hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook and cool pasta.
Add kidney beans and garbanzo beans to cooled pasta.
Slice or chop the vegetables, then add them to pasta.
Add Italian dressing and stir in.
Chill 1 hour.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Conventional Method:
Combine over hot (not boiling) water, chocolate morsels and milk.
Stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread into foil lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours).

title: raisin puffs with orange sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat until thick and clear.
Add 2 tablespoons butter; blend.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: creole chess pie
directions: Beat together until fluffy butter, sugar and eggs.
Add and mix well, cinnamon, nutmeg, vinegar, dates, nuts and coconut. Turn into pastry lined pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: cajun broiled chicken
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter (depending on how much chicken you are preparing).
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons of lemon juice and mix. Dip chicken in mixture to coat and sprinkle with seasoning.
Broil or grill.
Add more seasoning as you cook depending on how spicy you want it.
Pasta and pesto tastes good with this.

title: best-ever banana bread(quick bread)
directions: Measure and mix together dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Fold in dry ingredients and nuts.
Fill well-greased pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) about half full.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
This bread freezes well.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Cook beans until done.
Add all other ingredients together but the bacon.
Put bacon on top and bake at 400°, until dark and thick, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well; drop on wax paper with teaspoon.
Let cool and serve.

title: sweetheart cookies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
To speed chilling, divide dough and put into two pie tins lined with waxed paper for 1/2 hour.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Into each cookie, press a gumdrop half, cut side up.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat hard 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat
and add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Wash
and prepare vegetables.
Mix vegetables and cheese together
in
large
bowl (or keep separate so everyone can add
their
favorites).
Add meat mixture and chips.
Drop on sour cream and a few slices of olives.
Serve.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Combine pumpkin, salt, spices and King syrup.
Blend in milk. Add pudding.
Beat slowly until thick (about 1 minute).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in dish and chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: new dimension baked beans
directions: In a quart baking dish, combine all ingredients.
If desired, sprinkle with bacon pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Mix the flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine 1 egg, milk and melted oleo. Add to dry mixture. Spread in 9 x 9-inch square baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix together sour cream, coconut and sugar.
Refrigerate. Make up cake mix as directed on box.
Makes 2 (9-inch) layers. Cool and split layers, making 4 layers in all.

title: garbage cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until
light brown.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Mix boiling water and 100% Bran and let cool.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, buttermilk and soaked Nabisco 100% Bran. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add all at once with Kellogg's All-Bran.
Fold until all ingredients are moistened. You may add raisins or nuts.
Bake in greased muffin tins, 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
(You may store dough in covered dish in refrigerator for up to 7 weeks.)

title: chocolate roll
directions: Beat whites of eggs very stiff.
Add sugar and cocoa, then the yolks (well beaten).
Bake in jelly roll pan in moderate oven 20 minutes.
When cool, spread with Cool Whip.
Roll up like a jelly roll.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together into creamy mixture.
Put into baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: caramel apple cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar in mixing bowl until fluffy and well blended.
Spread on bottom of pie crust.
In skillet, over medium heat, melt butter and add apple.
Cook, stirring, until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Drain well on paper towels. Arrange apple slices on top of cheese, overlapping slices to fit. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Drizzle with warm caramel apple dip.

title: oatmeal cookies(a family favorite handed down many generations!)
directions: *You may decrease this amount and add nuts or raisins.

title: world's best meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs lightly and mix all ingredients with beef.
Shape mixture into a loaf and bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until meat is done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: nacho dip
directions: In a large saucepan melt cheese over medium to low heat.
Add ground beef, taco seasoning, salsa and chilies.
Serve in a fondue pot with tortilla chips.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut vegetables (carrots, potatoes, green beans, corn) into 1/2-inch cubes and steam until tender. Saute chopped onions, pepper and garlic (optional).

title: peanut sweet potato balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cornflakes; blend well. Shape into balls. Roll in cornflake crumbs. Place on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan. Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes (insert toothpick to see if comes clean). Cool 25 minutes in pan. Invert onto serving plate. Cool completely.

title: pumpkin pie (9-inch)
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and evaporated milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°. Bake an additional 40 to 50 minutes, or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: crustless pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix in crushed Ritz crackers. Add finely chopped nuts, sugar, salt and vanilla.
After mixing all together, pour into greased pie pan.
Cook at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients and the salt and pepper together.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt the margarine in a pan.
Stir in the sugar, egg, corn syrup, dates and nuts.
Cook until thick (about 20 minutes). Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Add the Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Make into balls.
Roll in coconut.
These keep well in refrigerator.
Very festive.

title: salt pickles
directions: Turn mixture over cucumbers, while hot, into a large container.
Let set for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate until chilled and ready to serve.
Pour over boiled shrimp on a bed of lettuce.

title: oatmeal bake
directions: Combine ingredients in a mixing bowl. Spoon into a 9 inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serve warm with a scoop of ice cream.

title: sand stars
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add 2 well beaten eggs; mix thoroughly.
Gradually add sifted flour and mix well again. Chill overnight.
Roll out thin on floured board or cloth; cut into shapes and place on greased baking sheet.
Brush tops with slightly beaten egg whites; sprinkle with mixture made of 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Press pecan half into center of each star. Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes or until edges of star points are lightly browned.
Makes 100 stars 2 1/2-inches across.

title: sugar free banana cream pie(deep dish)
directions: Prepare pudding and pie filling as per the directions on the box, using 2 percent milk.
Slice bananas and add to pie filling, after stirring the second time, then pour into baked pie shells. Let cool and top with lite Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: bacon and cucumber dip
directions: Peel and chop cucumber very fine.
Drain well.
Cut the bacon in small pieces and fry until crisp.
Drain off fat.
Add all ingredients and mix good.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: potatoes and toppings
directions: Scrub baking potatoes.
Rub skin with oil.
Wrap in foil. Bake in 400° oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
When done, cut in half.
Put condiments in bowls and serve with hot potatoes.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Add salt, sugar, lemon juice and rind.
When slightly thickened, beat in the whipped milk.
Put half of the crumbs in the bottom of the pan or dish (8 x 8-inch).
Pour in mixture and put rest of the crumbs on top.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Keeps several days.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Put chicken in electric skillet; pour rest of ingredients over top.
Cook at 200° until done, about 1 hour.

title: meat balls and spaghetti
directions: Mix hamburger and Italian sausage together in large bowl.
Add onion, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Mix well.
Make meat balls, approximately 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Fry meat balls until browned.
Mix Prego sauce, dry spaghetti seasoning and tomato sauce in another pan; heat.
Add water for desired thickness.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, vegetable oil and eggs.
Add vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Combine milk to soda in teaspoon, then add to pumpkin mixture. Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: In hot butter in large skillet, saute onion, garlic and beef chuck until meat is no longer red, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, basil, salt, pepper, sugar and 1 cup water; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: sugarless fruit bars
directions: Boil fruit in water for 5 minutes. Add 1 stick of margarine to fruit and set aside to cool. Mix remaining ingredients to make a batter. Add fruit mixture to batter and bake in a 9 x 13 pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream apple piestilwell, kansas
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and nutmeg into a large bowl.
Stir in beaten egg, sour cream and vanilla.
Wash, pare, quarter, core and slice apples thinly (about 2 cups).
Fold into sour cream mixture; spoon into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in a pre-heated hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to moderate (350°); bake 30 minutes longer.

title: marsala chicken (or fish)
directions: Coat chicken or fish with seasoned breadcrumbs.
Bake in pan coated with olive oil at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (less for fish).
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add onion, garlic, parsley and basil.
Stir in wine.
Cook 1 minute.
Quickly stir in bouillon and flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Take off burner.
Slowly stir yogurt into mixture, keeping sauce creamy. Add shiitake mushroom strips.
Stir in cheese.
Let simmer a few minutes.
Pour sauce over cooked chicken (1/2 to 1 cup per piece). Serve with pasta.

title: apricot balls
directions: Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: elephant stew
directions: Chop elephant into bite-size pieces, should take about 2 months.
Boil over wood fire for 2 weeks at 400°.
About 2 hours before serving, add chopped onions, salt and pepper.
This serves about 3,800 people.
If expecting more guests, add two rabbits. Do this only as a last resort, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: fresh baked king salmon from alaska
directions: Lay salmon flat in baking pan (9 x 12-inch).
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix equal amounts of mayonnaise and sour cream to cover the fish.
Sprinkle with dill spice and chives, then add the bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes (when fork flakes all the way through).
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Cook egg noodles; drain. Mix hamburger and noodles.
Add 1 can tomato soup and mix well. Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mix milk, sugar and eggs in a saucepan and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Then add bananas, salt and cream.
Churn until frozen.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well and press into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: scalloped hamburger
directions: Layer all items and cover and bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: speedy taco bake
directions: Pre heat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook ground beef and onion; drain.
Spoon into ungreased 13x9x2 baking pan.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake 35 minutes or until light golden brown.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce if desired. 8 to 10 servings.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Chill in shell at least 3 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, oil and oleo until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll into balls.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet.

title: sweet refrigerator pickles
directions: Add salt to sliced pickles and cover with boiling water.
Let set overnight and drain the next day. Mix and heat the vinegar, 1 cup sugar, celery seed, pickling spice and alum.
Put pickles in a 1 gallon jar and pour the heated mixture over the pickles.
Each morning, put 1 cup sugar in for 5 days.
Keep refrigerated.
Will stay good in the refrigerator for up to 1 year.

title: apricot delight
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple and baby food in blender container.
Blend on high for 30 seconds; set aside. Place gelatin, water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over a high heat. Add cream cheese mixture. Stir until well blended and allow to cool.
Fold whipped topping into mixture.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish with
chopped nuts. Refrigerate.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: In saucepan, combine butter and flour.
Add milk and stir until thick.
Stir in grated Cheddar cheese, salt and white pepper.
Roll one slice of ham around 4 stalks of asparagus, then place in greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch) seam side down.
When all are in place, pour cheese sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, lightly for color, before baking.

title: cheese danish
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll out 1 can of crescent rolls and place in pan.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in heavy saucepan.
Add milk and oleo. Bring to a boil.
Boil just 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Cool and beat until creamy.
Frost cake.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: curried chicken pita
directions: Cook chicken breast and cut up; chop celery.
Cut seedless grapes in half.
Mix all the ingredients together and fill the 4 halves of pita pockets.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onions.
Drain grease. Season with salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 green chili in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese.
Top with meat mixture. Add remaining chili and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients in blender and beat until smooth.
Pour over chili mixture.
Bake 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pot pie
directions: Filling:
Mix soup, seasoning, evaporated milk, meat and vegetables.
Spoon into casserole dish.

title: danish red cabbage(rod kal)
directions: Wash head; cut into 4 parts and remove inner stalk.
Shred cabbage thin and fine.
Melt butter in a large kettle.
Add vinegar, salt and sugar.
Add cabbage gradually, cooking slowly to soften, turning carefully with a spoon.
Add 1/2 cup currant jelly.
Let simmer, covered, for about 2 hours, turning occasionally.
A little water may be added during the cooking time.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and spread on bread.
Add 1/4 cup chopped nuts if desired.

title: dreamy cherry pretzel torte
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and blend.
Remove from heat; add pretzels and blend lightly.
Press mixture on bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, saving some for the top when finished.

title: bean and bacon bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the last two in a 2 1/2 qt. shallow casserole. On top of bean mixture, arrange Canadian bacon and orange slices in a ring. Refrigerate, covered.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Bring to a boil and cook until vegetables are tender.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Combine butter, onion, mustard and poppy seeds, mixing well. Spread on both sides of rolls.
Place ham slice and cheese on each roll.
Cover with top of roll.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bean soup (easy)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil. Mix all ingredients and heat and serve.

title: toogie's chicken casserole
directions: Mix grated Cheddar cheese, Parmesan cheese and red pepper. Set aside.
Cook noodles and drain.
Drain mushrooms and save juice.
Melt oleo in a large skillet and saute onions.
To this add seasonings and mushroom liquid.
Blend in soups and milk. Stir until thick. Add pimentos, mushrooms and half the cheese mixture. Pour this sauce over chicken and noodles and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with the rest of the cheese mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May be put together early in the day and baked a little longer.
Serve with English peas!

title: rocky road bar cookies
directions: Bake sugar cookie dough according to directions on package. Melt butter to water and stir in frosting mix; blend well and remove from heat.
Fold in marshmallows and spread mixture over cookie dough.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding the boiling water last. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Burn 1/2 cup white sugar in heavy iron skillet.
Add boiling water.
When sugar is amber color (do not scorch), let it cook down to a syrup and no lumps.
In same skillet, add milk, flour and eggs that have been mixed together.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
If too thick, add more milk.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add marshmallow cream. Bake at 350° until meringue is browned, about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine dates, hot water and baking soda in a bowl. Mix in another bowl, sugar, butter, egg, vanilla and half the hot water from bowl.
Mix in flour and salt.
Fold in remaining hot water and dates and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean in a greased and floured date-nut pan. Cool; remove from pan and wrap in foil wrap.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Mix and spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan, hamburger, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Over hamburger mixture with Tater Tots.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: veggie soup
directions: Heat oil in large, heavy pot.
Cook carrots, onions, garlic and leeks 15 minutes over low heat.
Fold in cabbage, potato and split peas; cook 10 minutes.
Add broth, 1/2 of parsley, thyme, tarragon and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add zucchini and cook 15 minutes.
Add spinach and cook 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and remaining parsley; cook 5 minutes longer.
Serves 8 to 10.
Best very hot with bread.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Chill about 1 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Press into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Whip the cream.
Blend softened cream cheese with powdered sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream to cream cheese mixture.
Spread on crust.
Top cream layer with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate 4 or more hours. Garnish with more whipped cream before serving.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees and grease a 12 cup muffin pan. Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda into a medium bowl and make a well in the center of the mixture.
In another bowl, mix milk, egg, oil, bananas and walnuts.
Pour mixture into well of flour.
Mix batter until just moistened, do not overmix.

title: broccoli nut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt per package directions; drain.
Add soup, mayo and water chestnuts or nut meats.
Mix well.
Add eggs and onion.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with grated cheese on top and buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shrimp st. remy
directions: In a skillet, melt the butter and saute the green onion and parsley just until they wilt. Blend in the flour. Add the milk slowly, stirring constantly, and cook until thick. Stir in the salt, pepper and mustard. Add the shrimp and cook gently just until the shrimp turn pink and are done. Remove the skillet from the heat and stir in the Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup of the Parmesan cheese. Spoon this into individual ramekins or a shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese and broil close to the heating element until the cheese browns. Serves 6.

title: chow mein
directions: Mix together and bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°, then 1 hour, uncovered.
May add water chestnuts and/or slivered almonds.

title: barbecue steak(workman's recipe)
directions: Dip strips of beef in flour and season; brown slightly with onion.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with chocolate buttercream icing.

title: hot peppers(canning recipe)
directions: Wash hot peppers.
Cut into rings and put in quart jars. Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour over peppers in the jars.
Put on lids and rings.
Set aside to seal.
Eat in about 2 months.

title: alberty's hot meat sandwiches
directions: Mix beef, potatoes, onion, parsley, bell pepper, celery, Ro-Tel, curry powder, pepper and salt thoroughly and bake in oven at 325° to 350° (mashing with a potato masher several times while cooking) until golden brown (approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour). Add butter, Cheddar cheese and chili and bake 30 minutes more. Best served with mustard on bread.

title: mexican flan
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and salt.
Beat in evaporated milk and vanilla.
Sprinkle brown sugar in bottom of loaf pan.
Gently pour mixture over brown sugar.
Place pan in shallow baking pan containing hot water.

title: vegetable platter
directions: Blanch asparagus, broccoli and cauliflower five minutes. Slice tomato.
Arrange on platter and keep cold.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook ground beef, oil, chopped onion and chopped green pepper until brown.
Stir in the can of tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, garlic salt, oregano, pepper and basil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook the noodles.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with bread slices.
Spread cheese mixture over bread.
Then place layer of meat (any kind you prefer).
Beat eggs and add milk; mix well. Pour over meat.
Put another layer of bread on top.
Bake one hour at 325° until puffy and brown.
Can be fixed night before and then baked in morning.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar together; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Pour remaining ingredients over crust and bake another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: merry marshmallows
directions: Pour sprinkles into a bowl.
Crush some graham crackers into another bowl.
These are what you will use to decorate your candy. Combine one 6 ounce bag of chocolate morsels with 2 teaspoons vegetable oil in microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High 1 minute, until melted; stir.
Poke a bamboo skewer or a fork into a marshmallow.
Dip into chocolate, coating it well.
Hold it over bowl to let excess chocolate drip off.
Coat marshmallow with sprinkles or graham cracker crumbs.
Slide marshmallow off skewer onto a waxed paper-lined baking sheet.
Repeat.
Let set at room temperature about 1 hour.
Wrap candies in a pretty box for a special gift.
Yield:
About 20 marshmallow candies.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Layer in your favorite casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake tarts
directions: Bake pastry shells according to package directions.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter; cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk; mix well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour, nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla; mix well.
Shape 1 tablespoonful (use measuring spoon) of dough around each piece of candy, covering completely.
Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet, 1 inch apart, for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cookies will be soft and appear shiny but become firm as they cool.
Do not overbake!
Remove from cookie sheet; cool.

title: pumpkin cooler
directions: Mix the vanilla ice cream, cooked pumpkin, milk and cinnamon in a glass.
When the mixture is liquid, you may drink.

title: scandinavian fried fish
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Set oil to heat in a large skillet until a few drops of water will spatter.
Beat the eggs in a pie plate.
In another pie plate, mix the flour, onion flakes, salt and pepper.
Dip fish sections into egg wash, then roll in seasoned flour until completely coated.
Gently dip fish into skillet.
Fry until fish is lightly browned on both sides and flakes easily.
Remove to a baking dish in the oven.
Saute onions in remaining fat.
Remove and spread over fish.
Pour bouillon over fish and bake for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6 happy people.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine pineapple concentrate, orange concentrate, lemonade concentrate, cranberry juice, ginger ale, ice water and lemon juice in a 6-quart mixing bowl.
Serve ice cold.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Clean wings and cut tips off.
Preheat oven.
I cook mine in a convection oven which requires no turning and makes it nice and crunchy, but a broiler also works fine.

title: meat loaf
directions: Crumble bread.
Add ground beef, onion, bell pepper, salt and tomato sauce.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Saute onions and green pepper in fat in heavy frying pan. Add beef and stir until brown and crumbly. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake 1 hour. Remove cover for the last 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large skillet, crumble meat with onion and garlic.

Break up pieces of meat with fork and cook until it loses its red color; drain. In slow cooker, combine browned meat with remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Serve over hot spaghetti. May be made ahead of time and frozen. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a heavy black iron frying pan. Bring to a boil on medium heat, stirring well.
This mixture scorches easily, so watch it.
Cook until peanuts start browning, begin to pop and smells good, then remove from heat and add soda. Stir well and pour out on 2 well buttered cookie sheets.
Use a spatula to smooth and spread it down.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook hamburg until brown.
Drain fat.
In a large kettle add hamburg, tomatoes, tomato paste, scallions, celery, bay leaf, wine and seasonings.
Simmer on low heat.

title: molded crab or shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add remaining items.
When it starts to congeal, stir in crab and/or shrimp, celery, onion, mayonnaise and pimento.
Garnish with lettuce, mayonnaise and ripe olives.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse the kidney and lima beans.
Add the other beans with liquid, carrots and onion.
Mix the oil, sugar, vinegar and salt together and pour over bean mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: quick dessert
directions: Whip cream; add sugar.
Mix the instant pudding by directions; fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip, then the fruit, juice and all.
Pour into individual dishes and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked onion rings
directions: Slice onions about 1/4-inch thick.
Separate into rings.
Soak in cold, salted water for 30 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: crusty peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 cup sugar. Set in oven to warm while mixing remaining ingredients.
Blend the butter and sugar together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture with milk.
Spread evenly over the peaches.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup sugar and dash of cinnamon, with 1/2 cup of water over the sugar.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until crusty and brown.

title: fried mozzarella
directions: Cut cheese into 1/2-inch cubes and dip into the egg.
Roll into the cracker crumbs.
Heat the oil in a skillet and fry the breaded cheese until crisp and brown.
Spear each cube with a toothpick.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° about 5 minutes.
Spread out to cover entire bottom of pan with fork, then cook about 25 minutes more or until light brown.
When done, stir it up and set aside to cool.
In large bowl, mix last 3 ingredients, beat 10 to 15 minutes to soft peak.
Fold in a carton of Cool Whip.
Pour over 2/3 crumb mixture in pan.
Save 1/3 crumb mixture to sprinkle over top.
Cover tightly and freeze.

title: molly's famous onion dip
directions: You will need 1 mixing bowl, 1 spoon.

title: creamy chocolate icing
directions: Measure all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until ingredients are well blended.
Makes 2 cups.

title: beef brisket
directions: My favorite for Sunday Dinner.
This was easy for me as I would put the meat in to cook before going to Church and would make the noodles and let them lay to dry while gone.
They would be ready to cut up and add to the beef broth and cook when I got home.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed.
When done while warm, prick with a fork.
Pour over cake while hot coconut oil.
When cool, spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: mrs. hoffman's rolls
directions: Mix in order given with electric beater.
You will have a soft batter.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Stir down and put in refrigerator to chill (about an hour).
Turn out on floured surface.
Roll out and cut into shapes.
Place on lightly greased baking tray.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients slightly and drain.
Add mayonnaise with Hidden Valley seasoning mix.
Mix together and chill.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop flowerets and smaller stems of broccoli.
Grate stalk. Discard outside stringy portion of stalk.
Stir in chopped onion and egg, relish and mayonnaise.
Let stand several hours or overnight to blend.
Best if chopped peanuts are added just before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta 10 minutes.
Add a little bit of salad oil and salt to water before boiling.
Drain and add ingredients.
Use your judgement on seasonings.

title: pioneer boulangerie lemon cake
directions: Combine yellow cake and
lemon	pudding
mix with eggs, oil and water and mix well 2 to 3 minutes on mixer.
Turn into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking
pan
or
tube pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes,
or
until
cake
springs back when lightly touched.
Separately,
combine
sugar,
lemon
juice, butter and water and
beat
until
smooth.
While warm, pierce surface of cake with a fork and pour icing evenly over top.

title: fake mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Put oatmeal in blender, blend to a flour consistency.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch to 2-inch balls, bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: oreo delight
directions: Crush cookies and set aside 2 cups.
Combine remaining crumbs with butter and line a 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture.
Slice ice cream and place on the crumbs.
Spread fudge over ice cream. Layer Cool Whip over fudge.
Sprinkle reserved Oreos on top.

title: dump bars
directions: Dump all ingredients together except chocolate chips.
Mix until all is moist.
Spread in greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake for moist bars.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread 1 can jalapeno bean dip onto a pizza pan.
Mix 1 cup sour cream with 1 package taco seasoning.
Spread this mixture on top of the bean dip.
Top with 1 small package Cheddar cheese, tops of green onions and sliced tomatoes.
Dip with nacho chips.

title: lazy day pie
directions: Heat the fruit.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and water together.
Pour the sugar, flour and water mixture into the baking dish on top of the butter.
Pour fruit on top of this and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare noodle soup, following directions on box except just add 4 cups of hot water and let stand while preparing the sausage.

title: swiss cheese and tomato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange croutons in 9-inch pie plate. Top croutons with tomato slices and then sprinkle with cheese.

title: fluffy "what"
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: beet jelly
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Remove beets from juice.
Add to juice Sure-Jell and lemon juice.
Boil 8 minutes.
Add sugar and jello.
Boil 10 minutes and pour into jars.
Seal.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Turn up the heat to 325° and bake another 30 minutes.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix together, by hand, all the ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crazy orange salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together cottage cheese, dry jello mix, Cool Whip, drained fruits and walnuts.
Chill before serving.

title: carrot dream cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Beat until lemon color and texture is smooth.
Sift flour and soda and beat into creamed mixture.
Add pineapple, carrots, nuts and coconut.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan well and put waxed paper on the bottom.
Pour in the batter.
Bake at 375 ° for 10 minutes and then at 350° until the cake is done, about 30 minutes.
Makes nice cupcakes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then stir in last 3 ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13-inch or Bundt pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dumplings
directions: Blend the egg with the flour and salt.
Add enough water to make a stiff dough.
Form into small ball and roll out dough.
Cut in small strips.
Drop into the boiling broth 15 minutes before serving.
Chopped parsley may also be added for extra flavor.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and almond in a 200° oven or in a microwave.
Add peanuts and mix.
Drop large teaspoonfuls on wax paper and let set up.

title: french onion soup
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, saute onions in butter until transparent
and
golden
brown.
Stir
in	beef
broth, water, sugar,
Worcestershire
sauce
and salt over high heat. Heat to boil, then	reduce	to
low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Meanwhile,	toast bread under broiler until light brown on both sides.
Arrange cheese slices on toast and broil until cheese is melted.
To serve, place cheese topped bread in each bowl and pour soup on top.

title: chocolate raspberry torte
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate and butter in double boiler. Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Whisk eggs, sugar, jam, brandy mixture and chopped semi-sweet chocolate.

title: savory roulades or chicken roll-ups
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons oil; add onion, celery and bread crumbs. Cook until celery is glazed and crumbs brown.
Add seasonings; remove from heat.
Add egg.
Place 2 tablespoons of filling on flattened chicken.
Roll up from wide end, folding in to hold filling.
Put in greased pan; add wine.
Use 2 tablespoons oil with wine to bake.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: fluffy funnel cakes
directions: Beat egg with milk; stir in flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Hold finger under funnel and fill 1/4 cup full of batter.
Start in center of hot oil, move in circle to make snail-like coil of rings.
Remove when golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sweet 'n sour turkey potato salad
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar and vinegar.
Heat until the sugar dissolves.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add onion, salt, pepper, ketchup and mayonnaise.
Add the potatoes, celery and turkey.
Toss well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheesed hash browns
directions: Mix hash browns, cheese, soup and onion together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and drizzle over potato mixture. Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or 350° for 1 hour.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg and mix well.
Add milk and mix well.
Add the baking powder, flour and vanilla.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna-chicken pie
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook, stirring until mixture thickens and boils.
Add remaining ingredients except biscuit mix.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Prepare biscuit mix.
Arrange rounds on top of hot tuna mixture.
Bake in oven at 425° for about 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian kielbasa
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch rings. Drain olives, cherries and pineapple; put into crock-pot or casserole pan. In small bowl, mix brown sugar and mustard together.

title: hoover's orange julius
directions: Place ice cubes in blender.
Add sugar and orange juice concentrate, then remaining ingredients.
Blend 1 minute; stir. Blend 2 minutes until smooth.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar, molasses and 1 egg. Alternately add the coffee with the dry ingredients.
Mix all together, chill overnight.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick, cut and bake at 375° for 14 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken; remove bone and tear apart.
Put small amount on crescent roll and roll from large end.
Spray casserole dish with Pam and put rolls in.
Beat egg and mix with next 4 ingredients. Pour over top of roll-ups.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until brown.

title: friendship cake starter
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a glass gallon jar; let set for 2 weeks, covered loosely with foil with a wooden spoon inserted through the foil to stir daily.
Do not remove foil or spoon.
Be sure to stir daily.
After 2 weeks, add the next 3 ingredients; let set 2 more weeks, stirring daily.
In the fourth week, add the next 3 ingredients; stir daily.
In the sixth week, strain fruit from the juice using a plastic strainer (do not use metal).
You may use fruit for ice cream topping.
Juice is starter for Friendship Cake.

title: chicken fettuccine alfredo
directions: In large pot filled with boiling water, prepare pasta according to directions on package.
When pasta reaches al dente stage, remove from heat and drain.
Place pasta in large serving bowl and set aside.
Brown both sides of chicken in oil 2 minutes, or until meat is just done.
Put chicken in bowl with pasta.
Add onion and garlic to skillet and saute until tender.
Reduce heat to low and stir in wine.
Add chicken base and simmer 1 minute. Stir in cream.
Add cheese, pepper and parsley.
Simmer 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour hot sauce over pasta and chicken, tossing to coat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hominy salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over hominy and stir together.
Chill and serve.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook pasta; dice onion, cucumber and tomatoes.
Add to linguini.
Add Salad Supreme; add dressing.
Mix together and chill 2 hours.

title: quick jello parfaits(almost sugar-free)
directions: Pour boiling water into blender container.
Add gelatin; blend at low speed until dissolved, about 30 seconds.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin; stir until ice is partially melted, then blend at high speed for 10 seconds.
Add whipped topping; blend 15 seconds.
Pour half the mixture into 6 straight sided dessert glasses, then fill glasses with remaining mixture.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let set at least 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 30 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: coffee 'n' cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Slowly beat in melted butter, sugar, vanilla, nutmeg and Grand Marnier.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: holiday bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over the lukewarm water and let stand 5 minutes. Add lukewarm milk and then the sugar, shortening, salt and mace. Stir.
Beat in the eggs. Gradually add the flour and mix well.
Turn the dough out on a floured board and knead until it is smooth and elastic.
Place dough in a greased bowl, cover with a towel and allow to rise in a warm place until it is doubled in bulk. Divide dough in half, then each half in 3 parts so that there are 6 pieces.
On a lightly floured board, form each piece into a roll 12-inches long.
On a greased cookie sheet, braid 3 of the rolls together.
Form the second braid on another sheet. Allow the braids to rise until they are doubled in bulk.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in water in saucepan.
Add to stuffing, mixing well.
Add egg and sausage and blend thoroughly.
Chill for 1 hour for easier handling, then shape into small oblongs about the size of a pecan log.
Cut bacon slices into thirds.
Wrap each piece of the stuffing mixture with bacon and fasten with toothpicks.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Note:
I grate an apple into mine, optional.

title: cube steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak in bite size pieces.
Roll in flour and brown.
Add 2 teaspoons steak sauce, 1 cup sour cream, 1 or 2 cans mushroom soup and 1 or 2 cans water to fried steak.
Season with chopped onions or onion flakes.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crab quiche
directions: Set oven to 325°. Place pie shell in oven for 5 minutes. Remove. Place crabs and bacon in bottom of shell. Combine all other ingredients and pour over crab and bacon. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: lazy lasagna(lighter eating - 8 points)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook meat in large nonstick skillet over med-high heat until browned, stirring to crumble. Drain well, and return meat to pan. Add sauce, bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 5 minutes. Combine cottage and parmesan cheeses in a bowl; set aside. Spread 1/2 c. meat mixture in bottom of 13 X 9 inch baking dish coated with cooking spray. Arrange 4 noodles over meat mixture; top with half of cottage cheese mixture, 1 c. meat mixture; and 1/3 c. cheddar cheese. Repeat layers, ending with noodles. Spread remaining meat mixture over noodles. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover, sprinkle with 1/3 c. cheddar cheese, and bake 5 more minutes or until cheese melts. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: potato chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes and chicken.
Add salt, pepper and flour.
Sprinkle over chicken and potatoes.
Melt butter.
Add to soup and milk mixture.
Pour over potato mixture.
Top with crushed chips or crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven, covered.
Remove cover and bake for 15 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican dip
directions: Warm all ingredients
in crock pot. Serve over tortilla chips. Enough for a crowd.

title: beer-cheese triangles
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together packaged biscuit mix and shredded cheese.
Make a well in the center.
Add beer all at once.
Stir just until mixture clings together.
Knead gently on a lightly floured surface for 5 strokes. Roll or pat dough into a 6-inch circle. Cut into 10 wedges.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve each package with 1 cup of boiling water.
Divide in halves.
To 1/2 cup in a bowl, add 2 tablespoons water.
To the other 1/2 in another bowl, add 3 tablespoons sour cream.
Put the first half in 9-inch square pan or mold and let set until firm. Add the other half; then in the meantime, dissolve second package and repeat the steps.
As 1 layer sets, firmly, add another alternate color.

title: braised fish
directions: Dust fillets lightly with flour.
In a heavy skillet, heat oil and brown fish on both sides.
Combine sugar, garlic, and ginger with soy sauce, sherry and enough water to make 1 cup.
Pour over fish, cover and braise 10 minutes.
Uncover, add black pepper, chives, parsley and chopped tomatoes.
Cook, uncovered, another 5 minutes.
Mix together cornstarch, salt and water, blend well. Simmer 5 minutes more.

title: japanese chicken wings
directions: Cut off pointed end of wings. Dip in egg and flour and brown in oil. In saucepan, simmer next 5 ingredients for 2 minutes. Put browned wings in glass baking dish and pour sauce over wings. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Spooning sauce over wings while they bake. Best when baked long enough where sauce turns thick.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat and onion in skillet and drain.
Stir in soup, vegetables and milk. Set aside.
In greased pan, stir Bisquick and water until moistened and spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Spoon beef mixture over batter.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jello-cool whip dessert
directions: Line pan or dish with plastic.
Whip Jell-O; let set until starting to jell.
Break up baked cake into cubes and drop into Jell-O; mix.
Add 1/2 container Cool Whip.
Let jell to firm, then spread the remaining Cool Whip on top of Jell-O mixture.
Leave in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Place 4 scoops (about 1/2 cup each) ice cream in a small pan. Freeze for 1 hour or until firm.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together egg and vanilla.
In a pie plate carefully stir together cereal and cinnamon.
Dip each frozen ice cream ball in egg mixture, then roll it in cereal mixture.
Return coated ice cream balls to pan and freeze for 1 hour or until firm.
Reserve remaining cereal mixture.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Store in Tupperware at room temperature.
Use for pancakes, biscuits and waffles.

title: tate's zucchini bake
directions: Saute ground beef in a skillet until browned.
Add peppers, garlic and onions and cook for another 2 minutes.
While meat is cooking, make corn muffin mix batter according to directions. Place half of the batter in a greased bread pan.
Over the batter, place a layer of the meat mixture.
Add a layer of zucchini, then cheese.
Keep layering until mixture is gone.
Finally, add the rest of the corn muffin mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: In large bowl, cream together shortening, 1 cup sugar.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, spices and salt.
Add to first mixture. Mix well.
Cover and chill.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Roll each in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° about 8 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack and cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: hamburger-corn bake
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In a frypan melt butter and add bread crumbs.
Brown bread crumbs and set aside.
In a skillet, cook beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in soup, corn, sour cream, milk, pimiento, salt and pepper; mix well.
Stir in the noodles.
Turn mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 50 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Crush half of the strawberries, using the smaller ones.
Add sugar, cornstarch and lemon juice and cook until thick.
Put the remaining berries in bottom of pie crust.
Pour mixture over berries.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Combine all liquid ingredients in medium saucepan.
Simmer. Add onion, cheese, broccoli and rice.
