Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lobster(excellent!  goes great with clams!)
directions: You will also need Pam cooking spray.

title: frosty fruit salad
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Stir in whipped topping, dressing and juice.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Freeze overnight. Unmold onto serving platter.
Serve with assorted fresh fruit. Makes 12 servings.

title: toothpick spicy shrimp
directions: Chop onion and garlic.
Soften in one ounce butter.
Remove from pan.
Add livers and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Cool and chop finely; add onions and sieve.
Stir in remaining 2 ounces butter and brandy.
Pack into buttered mold. Chill.
Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: potato soup(low-fat)
directions: Cook vegetables in broth until tender, then blend in a blender or use a potato masher to blend vegetables.
Add 1 pint of low-fat milk or skimmed milk.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Heat and serve in mugs or bowls.
Sprinkle no-fat cheese on top.

title: semas ranch kahlua cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, eggs, oil and Kahlua.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until it tests done.
This cake is rich, moist and delicious!

title: chocolate cherries
directions: *Add a little milk to chocolate bits when melting.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli, mushrooms and green onions.
Cut cherry tomatoes in half.
Mix all ingredients together and pour salad dressing over vegetables.
Mix well to make sure vegetables are all coated.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Put in buttered dish.
Cover with topping.

title: pastry mix
directions: Mix flour, salt and 2/3 of the Crisco together until fine. Add remaining Crisco and mix until very coarse.
Store indefinitely in airtight container.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and salad dressing.
Stir in cranberry sauce and drained pineapple.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pantry casserole
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan layer vegetables in order given; make 2 layers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with croutons.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled red beets
directions: Wash beets and cut tops, leaving 1-inch of stems and entire root.
Cook until tender.
Slip skins and cut into desired size pieces.
Bring to boil with remaining ingredients.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars and fill with boiling liquid.
Seal.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix limeade with syrup.
Add Cool Whip and green food coloring.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Freeze or chill.
I prefer this recipe frozen.

title: mag's party ham rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Cut rolls in half.
Spread sauce on the bottom half.
Add ham and cheese. Cover with top half of roll.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening together.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour and cream of tartar with 5 cups flour 2 or 3 times.
Keep 6th cup of flour to use if needed.
Add vanilla.
Make into rolls. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Let the water, sugar and dates come to a boil, then add the soda and boil for 10 minutes.
Then, add the lard, flour, pecans and fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add frozen berries and mashed bananas.
Pour half into dish.
Let stand until firm.
Spread sour cream over layer and add remaining mixture (that has been standing in hot water).
Let stand until firm.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine beef, cracker crumbs, milk, garlic salt, salt, pepper and onion.
Form into balls and brown in frying pan (can be browned in oven).

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix 1/2 of nuts and parsley.
Reserve for later use.
Mix all other ingredients to a smooth consistency and chill until the cheese mixture can be rolled into a ball.
Roll ball in nut and parsley mixture and serve with crackers.

title: pink lady
directions: Put all ingredients except mint into blender and blend until frothy and well mixed.
Pour into chilled 12 ounce glass. Garnish with a fresh raspberry and mint sprig.
Serves 1.

title: peanuts - roasted and sugared
directions: Mix
sugar
and
water	in heavy skillet.
Add peanuts. Cook on	medium	heat
until
all
syrup cooks away and leaves peanuts sugared.
Pour in buttered pan and sprinkle with salt. Cook in 300° oven about 30 minutes, stirring often.
Sprinkle once more lightly with salt.

title: chinese noodles and pork
directions: Fry onion, ginger root, garlic and bacon.
Add pork chops and soy sauce.
Cook until pork is done.
Add sugar, seasonings and pineapple juice.
Cook noodles in boiling water.
Drain.
Add to pork mixture.
Garnish with celery and pineapple slices.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring mixture to a boil.
This can be served immediately and/or stored in the refrigerator.

title: zesty italian potatoes
directions: Wash
and
scrub
potatoes (leaving peeling on).
Slice potatoes in even slices and layer in a large casserole dish (2 layers).
Pour
Zesty
Italian
dressing over the potatoes and bake at 350° until potatoes are tender. Serve hot.

title: hamburger and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain and rinse.
Cook hamburg; add all ingredients except noodles.
Put noodles in greased casserole and cover with meat mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pork-a-roni
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water and drain.
Cut pork, green pepper and onion in pieces and fry brown in butter.
Combine all ingredients in buttered baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll in snipped parsley (fresh).
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: spicy apple delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
Empty mix into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix, bake and cool.

title: 7-layer mexican dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Mix together avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine ingredients and form into crust.
Bake.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Whip the cream cheese in a bowl until smooth.
Add Marshmallow Fluff and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with apple wedges, strawberries, grapes and melon chunks or any other favorite fruit.

title: orange banana slush
directions: Boil water and sugar until dissolved.
Add other ingredients and freeze solid.
About an hour before serving, remove from freezer to soften.
Use potato masher or pastry blender to "slush" it.
Mix with 2 liters of lemon lime or ginger ale pop.

title: oreo pie
directions: Soften ice cream with mixer and add Cool Whip, mixing until well blended.
Fold in crushed Oreos.
Pour into oblong pan and freeze.

title: spaghetti with turkey meat sauce
directions: Spray a large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Preheat over high heat.
Add turkey; cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomatoes with their juice, green pepper, onion, garlic, oregano and black pepper.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove cover.
Simmer for 15 minutes more.
Cook spaghetti according to package.
Drain well.
Makes 6 servings. Calories 330, total fat 5 g.

title: super supper slaw
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Stir in raisins and cabbage; toss with mayonnaise.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Coarsely chop cucumber. Squeeze in paper towel to remove as much moisture as possible.
Same with the onion.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve on small bread or cut into triangles.

title: egg souffle(serves 12)
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam spray.
Remove the crusts from bread and cut into cubes.
Layer the bread, cheese and optional additions.
Continue layers.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over layers.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: bewitched cake(microwave)
directions: Grease 2 glass 8-inch square baking dishes.
Line with 2 sheets wax paper; grease.
Cover corners with foil.
In large bowl of electric mixer, beat first 6 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate pieces, pour into baking dishes.
Place one dish on inverted bowl, cook on Medium for 8 minutes, rotating dish every 2 minutes.
Remove foil; cook on High for 4 minutes, rotating dish every 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Repeat for second layer. Invert layers onto rack.
Cool.

title: spiced oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Add eggs, oil and sugar. Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Take off heat and add mushrooms, rice and soups in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: In slow cooker, mix all ingredients, stirring constantly, until hot and mixed well.

title: rancherittos
directions: Combine oil, dill weed, lemon pepper and Ranch dressing mix in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over crackers and pretzels; toss to coat well.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes. Cool to room temperature. Store in airtight container.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Rinse sauerkraut in water and drain.
Cut potatoes in half. Heat oil in a skillet over medium heat.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper and brown them on both sides, about 4 minutes in all; set aside.
Put potatoes in the same side and brown the cut side, about 2 minutes; remove from skillet.
Add sauerkraut, 1/4 tsp. salt, 1/2 tsp. pepper and caraway seeds.
Top with chops and potatoes, pressing them into the sauerkraut.
Lower heat.
Cover pan and simmer until the chops are very tender, about 40 minutes. Taste for seasoning and add salt and pepper if needed.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt the almond bark and chocolate chips in double boiler. Add peanuts; drop onto greased cookie sheets lined with wax paper. This can be melted in the microwave, also.

title: dream cake
directions: Grease and flour pans.
Bake cake according to directions on cake box.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Stir well, then spoon into casserole dish (which has been sprayed with Pam).
Bake approximately 45 minutes (covered with foil) at 350°.
Remove foil and brown.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops in skillet.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients; pour over chops.
Simmer (stir or baste chops with mixture often) for 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Serve with beds of fluffy rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly, except pecans.
Chill several hours.
Shape into balls.
Roll in the chopped pecans.
Chill; serve with crackers.

title: hot cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in 5-quart saucepan.
Bring to a simmer.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove spices with slotted spoon.
Pour into warm cups.
Makes 20 servings.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Combine eggs, half and half, salt and thyme; set aside.

title: suet pudding or plum pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two 1 pound coffee cans. Cover with wax paper before pudding lid on.
Steam slowly for 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Separately prepare broccoli and Rice-A-Roni mix according to directions.
Place cooked broccoli and Rice-A-Roni in 4-quart crock-pot.
Add cream of chicken soup to broccoli and Rice-A-Roni and stir.
Cube the cheese and mix in.
Allow time in heated crock-pot for cheese to melt and serve.
Makes approximately 32 (4 ounce) servings.

title: manicotti
directions: Combine all ingredients except marinara sauce and manicotti shells.
Pour 1/2 jar marinara sauce in pan.
Place stuffed shells on top of sauce in pan.
Pour rest of marinara sauce on top. Rinse jar with 1/2 cup of water and pour over manicotti.
Cover and cook 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover; sprinkle with a little Mozzarella and cook until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Knead all together and make into small balls.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: cheesy crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and rub skins with oil.
Bake until tender (or microwave.)
Cut potatoes in half, and scoop out inside into a mixing bowl.
Add cheese, butter, milk, onions and red pepper. Drain crab and pick out any shells.
Add crab to potato mixture and mash together.
Stuff potato shells.
Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.
Bake in 350 degree oven until hot. (About 25 minutes.) Serve as a meal or with charcoaled steaks.
Serves 4.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Add flour, if needed, to make a stiff dough.
Turn onto floured board; knead lightly.
Roll and cut into 16 biscuits.
Place onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Let rise.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add rest of ingredients.
Take a teaspoonful of dough and roll in a ball.
Press with a fork on top. Bake until light brown at 350°.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute shrimp in butter and seasonings for 1 minute on each side until translucent look goes away.
Add wine and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and stir until crumbs are moist with butter. Serve on a bed of rice.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute meat and onions (salt).
Then add the mushroom soup, chicken soup and enchilada sauce.
Then add chili peppers, diced. Grease a large casserole dish.
Put layer of Doritos, then layer mixture until all have been used.
Add cubed cheese to top.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: unbelievable cookies
directions: Mix and set aside for 10 minutes.
Roll in balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet; slightly flatten with fork and crisscross. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan for a few minutes before removing to wire rack.

title: nut babovka
directions: Cream the butter and powdered sugar together. Add beaten yolks. Add sifted flour and baking powder alternately with milk, beating until smooth. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Add lemon rind and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: salad (or dessert)
directions: In saucepan, combine vanilla pudding and lemon Jell-O in 2 cups water.
Cook until comes to boil.
Add lemon juice.
Chill until partially set (not able to be poured).
Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Beat in cranberry sauce; fold in celery and nuts.
Chill.
Fold whipped topping into pudding mix. Pour 1/2 pudding mix in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until set. Pour in all of cranberry mix.
Chill.
Top with remainder of pudding mix.
Chill overnight.
Prepare 1 day ahead.

title: beef roll-up appetizers
directions: Combine cream cheese and horseradish.
Spread mixture on double dried beef slices; roll up.
Chill and serve.

title: cindy's incredible fudge
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt cheese and butter until smooth. Remove from heat.
Add sugar, cocoa and vanilla and mix well. Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Slice peeled cucumbers into a bowl or jar. Sprinkle sugar over cucumbers; add vinegar and water. Sprinkle dried dill weed on top. Let marinate 48 hours. Mix several times during that time.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 370° to 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole(a side dish)
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs in a large bowl.
Pour mixture into round casserole. Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over the top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
After baking, let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: festive shrimp and fettucini
directions: In skillet over medium heat, cook shrimp in hot butter with green pepper, onion, garlic and red pepper until shrimp turn pink. Stir in soup, water and vinegar.
Heat thoroughly.
Season to taste.
Serve over fettucini or favorite pasta.
Serves 4.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the shortening and add sugar. Add beaten egg, molasses and dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked shell.
Put on cookie sheet and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Very tasty with cubes of Hawaiian sweet bread or spread on bread sticks, too.

title: apple delish
directions: Pour pie filling in 1-inch deep baking pan.
Distribute the dry cake mix evenly over pie filling.
Melt butter and let cool; spoon melted butter evenly over cake mix.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Mix together into a ball.
Roll in crushed pecans.

title: apricot upside-down pudding(4 to 5 persons)
directions: Soak the apricots overnight if possible.
Chop the suet finely and mix with the flour, salt, baking powder, sugar and cinnamon. Grease a cake tin and decorate the bottom with apricots.
Chop the remaining fruit and add to the flour, etc.
Mix with milk.
Place in the cake tin; cover with greased paper and steam for 2 hours. Serve with custard.
(WCB)

title: cucumber relish
directions: Cook 20 minutes and put in jars and seal.

title: courtney's favorite shrimp and rice
directions: In a pan, cook green pepper, onion, garlic and thyme in butter. Add soup, shrimp and water.
Heat and serve over cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl and pour drink over the sherbet. Stir until sherbet is in real small pieces.

title: pie shell
directions: Mix and roll on floured surface.
Yields 1 crust.

title: crazy pizza
directions: Mix flour, oregano, salt, pepper, eggs and milk until smooth. Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Add desired meat topping, vegetables, mushrooms, onions, peppers, etc.
Bake 20 minutes in 425° oven.
Top with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Shape into meat balls.
Fry in small amount of fat until brown.

title: fish chowder
directions: Bring a small quantity of water to boil in a soup pot.
Add celery, onion, leeks and garlic and cook until vegetables are tender and slightly yellowed.
Add the carrot, canned tomatoes with juice, tomato sauce, parsley, bay leaf, thyme, pepper and 1 cup of water.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat on low and simmer slowly, covered, for about 15 minutes or until fish is cooked and flavors are well blended.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Soak unpeeled, diced apples in pineapple juice to keep them from turning brown.
Drain.
Toss with remaining fruit.
Chill.

title: old fashioned apple pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 6 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: chicken and pineapple
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in flour, coating well.
Brown in hot oil
over medium heat.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan;
sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Mix and put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole the night before and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and pepper very fine.
Place in flat pan, such as a Pyrex 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with boiling water and let stand one hour; drain and return to pan.

title: glazed acorn squash
directions: Cut squash into 1-inch crosswise slices.
Remove seed and stringy fibers from center.
Arrange slices in 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High setting for 6 minutes.
Turn squash over and rearrange slices.
Cover tightly and microwave at High setting 6 minutes more, or until tender.
Drain squash.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake in 4 small or 2 very large loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot rise biscuits
directions: Sift flour and sugar into bowl.
Make well in flour.
Combine 1/4 cup of warm water and dry yeast; dissolve well.
Fill to 1 cup with buttermilk.
Add Crisco.
Pour into flour well and mix. Make 8 biscuits.
Turn over on buttered cookie sheet.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 450°.

title: peanutty chocolate surprises
directions: Cream peanut butter, margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs. Combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon, gradually adding to peanut mixture until well blended.
Chill dough at least 30 minutes.
Wrap about 1 level teaspoon of dough around each chocolate piece.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to wire racks and cool slightly. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: crock-pot corn
directions: Cook on high for 2 1/2 hours.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown the chops after seasoning with seasoned salt.
After the chops have been browned on both sides, cover with water, bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer.
Place the lid slightly askew on the Dutch oven.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add water if needed.
Next, add the sauerkraut and continue to simmer for another 30 minutes.
Do not let water boil away.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
Cover the chops and potatoes with sauerkraut.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Press 1 cup crumb mix onto sides and bottom of an ice cube tray.
Chill.
In top of double boiler or saucepan prepare filling or pudding, adding sugar, salt, 3 egg yolks, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Cook until thick.
Cool.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Soak lima beans overnight.
Cook slowly and drain.
Combine next 6 ingredients; add to cooked beans.
Top with bread crumbs and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and pepper pasta
directions: Boil shrimp, peel and set aside.
May use cooked, if necessary. Saute sliced peppers in olive oil. Add sun-dried tomatoes. Add minced garlic last so as not to burn. Begin to simmer for 10 minutes, then add shrimp.
Continue to simmer 10 or more minutes on medium-low heat.
Boil bow tie pasta or any pasta you prefer and drain.
Spoon heated mixture over pasta and serve.

title: martin warner's fudge sauce
directions: Melt and mix butter and chocolate.
Add sugar and flavorings. Slowly whisk in cream and milk.
Serve hot; store in fridge.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl mix corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour buttermilk into a 1-quart measuring cup.
Add eggs and beat with a fork.
Add melted butter and soda. Just before you are ready to bake, put lump of butter in 9-inch square pan or No. 10 cast-iron skillet.
Put in oven to melt. Combine dry ingredients with buttermilk-egg mixture until just blended.
Mixture should thin enough to pour.
You may need to add more buttermilk.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until light golden brown on top.
Serve hot with butter.

title: easy chocolate mousse
directions: In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over cold water; let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Stir in butter until melted.

title: health bread
directions: Stir together oats, graham flour, bran, raisins, water, salt, sugar, soda, buttermilk and egg.
Stir well and turn into greased loaf pan.

title: spinach dip with pumpernickel bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut out the inside of the pumpernickel bread.
Fill bread with spinach dip.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and put in a casserole to bake.
May be made ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to cook.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted is clean.
Serves about 6.

title: sausage cheese muffins
directions: Combine sausage, onion & green pepper in skillet. Cook over medium heat until sausage is brown, stirring to crumble. Drain.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thickened. Remove from heat. Add the Jell-O (dry).
Mix well.
Pour over the strawberries.
Pour into baked pie crust. Chill and serve with Cool Whip.

title: chicken divan
directions: Combine chicken and water to cover in a large saucepan; cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Drain well.
Chop chicken.
Set aside.

title: ham au gratin
directions: Mix ham, tomatoes, peppers and cheese.
Put in casserole dish. Make white sauce.
In small saucepan melt butter, stir in flour; slowly add milk and stir.
Add salt, Tabasco and dry mustard.
Pour sauce over ham mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour on top 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 2 cups boiling water, 2 tablespoons (lump) butter.
Mix together.
Stick with fork while baking at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: mom's pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Heat oven to 300°. Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Measure and sift flour together. Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, 2 at a time, blending at least 1 minute after each addition.
Add vanilla; blend 2 more minutes.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: bread rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine hot milk, shortening, sugar and salt to melted shortening.
Cool to lukewarm by adding cold water.
Stir in mixed eggs and yeast.
Mix approximately 6 cups flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise to double in size.
Add sifted flour to make a stiff dough, approximately 6 to 7 cups. Knead dough until smooth.
Shape into buns by pinching off dough about the size of an egg.
Roll between hands and place on a cookie sheet but not touching.
Let rise to double in size.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water 10 minutes.
Add soda.
Remove from heat.
Pour over jello, sugar and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
When slightly thickened, add celery and nuts. Refrigerate until served.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
In a separate bowl, mix flour and brown sugar together.
Place first 6 ingredients in a baking dish.
Pour flour and brown sugar mixture over top.
Pour 1/3 cup melted butter over and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Combine meat, apple juice, consomme, salt, pepper and onion in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix flour and crumbs and stir into beef. Bake 3 hours in 300° oven.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: swiss steak
directions: Season flour with salt and pepper; pound flour into steak. Brown meat in oil.
Drain meat.
Set aside.
Crush whole tomatoes in juice in skillet.
Add onion and peppers.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add steak and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: sombrero spread
directions: Brown meat and 1/4 cup chopped onion in skillet.
Stir in ketchup, chili powder and salt.
Add beans, including liquid; mash to mix thoroughly with other ingredients.
Heat.
Garnish with shredded cheese, remaining 1/2 cup chopped onion and olives. Serve with corn chips.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on the bottom of 1 (10 x 13-inch) baking pan.
Cook ground beef in skillet with onion.
Add Season-All.
Drain off fat and add taco seasoning mix, dry, to meat mixture.
Pour meat on top of cheese in pan.
Spread evenly. Add refried beans to top of meat mixture.
Add chilli.
Spread on top of meat mixture.
Shred Cheddar cheese or taco cheese.
Spread on top of meat mixture.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Take cover off; cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: corn chowder
directions: Blend 2 1/2 cups corn until smooth; set aside.
Melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onion and next 3 ingredients.
Saute 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add potato and broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes or until potato is tender.
Add the corn puree and remaining 1 1/2 cups corn.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: biscuit pizza
directions: Spread biscuits in glass dish until they cover the bottom of dish.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Pour sauce over hamburger and half of Cheddar cheese.
Pour over biscuits and put the rest of cheese on top and bake until brown.

title: parmesan appetizer loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, egg, 1/4 cup butter and 2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: coconut pecan filling
directions: Combine milk, sugar, butter, flour and vanilla in saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat until thickened. Remove from heat. Stir in coconut. Beat until thickened and cooled. Yield: Enough for a 3-layer cake.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Mix Bix-Mix and water.
Add eggs, mustard and 1 cup cheese; mix well.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and dot with butter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Slice and serve while warm.

title: herbed rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine about 5 minutes.
Stir in rice and cook until rice is coated with butter and translucent.
Add water to broth to make 2 cups.
Stir into rice.
Add bay leaf, thyme, rosemary and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 20 minutes until rice is tender and liquid absorbed. Remove bay leaf.
Stir in nuts, if desired, and parsley.

title: fiery chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Cut into serving pieces.
Peel and chop onions.
In a skillet, heat butter.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time.
Saute until well browned on all sides.
Add onions.
Saute a few more minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir to combine.
Cover.

title: merry christmas balls
directions: Mix well!
Roll in ball.
Mash 1/2 cup or 1 cup of nuts and roll ball in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: snappy tomato pizza
directions: Pick up telephone receiver.
Ask for Kevin. Order your favorite pizza.
Wait 15 minutes for the best pizza in town.

title: quick broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup and sour cream with broccoli, pimento and celery. Pour mixture into baking dish and top with cup of Cheddar cheese. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: skoley's creamed corn
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and bread crumbs.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Pour in casserole dish.
Mix crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in punch bowl.
Spoon sherbet in and mix lightly.
Serve immediately

title: helen's meat loaf
directions: Chop or grind all vegetables.
Mix well with meat, seasonings, eggs and bread crumbs.
If too dry, add 1/4 cup milk and 1/4 cup catsup.
Mix until you can shape into loaves.
Put into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: baked chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Mix mushroom soup, mushrooms, sour cream and flour.
Pour over chicken and cook at 350° for 2 hours.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in seasoning and water; cook 15 minutes.
Pat rolls in a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Layer as follows:
One cup corn chips, meat, spread with sour cream, Cheddar cheese and remaining 1 cup chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grilled pot roast
directions: Tenderize roast with fork.
Pour Bouquet and soy and shake salt, pepper and dry mustard on both sides of pot roast.
Work seasonings into meat with fingers.
Line bottom of pan with sliced onion.
Place roast in pan and put more onion on top.
Add a small amount of water.
Cook on low in gas grill.
Just before done, place directly on grill for a couple minutes.
Save drippings to pour over roast.

title: layered cabbage
directions: In a large pot, starting with the cabbage, layer the vegetables, ending with the cabbage.
Cover with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add margarine or desired meat for seasoning. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Butter or spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cut enough summer squash or zucchini into slices or chunks.
Fill until baking dish is heaping full.
Take squash out and put in a pan of water. Cook for 10 minutes, covered.
Drain and put squash back into casserole baking dish.
Saute small onion in butter.
Add soup and cheese.
Add evaporated milk to soup mixture.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: honey-peanut squares
directions: Butter square pan (8 x 8 x 2).
Heat honey and sugar just to boiling in a 3-quart pan over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Fold in cereal and peanuts.
Press firmly in pan.
Let stand at least 1 hour.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and let dry.
Add water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, sliced eggs, crumbled bacon and sliced fresh mushrooms.
Toss lightly.
(Grilled chicken breast strips may be placed on top of salad to be used as a meal.)
Serve with Spinach Salad Dressing.

title: teenage delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onion.
Layer 1/2 package Tater Tots in a 5-quart casserole dish; add 1/2 mixture of beef to top of Tots.
In separate bowl, mix soup and milk until smooth. Layer 1/2 of soup mixture to top of beef; add 1/2 shredded cheese. Repeat these 4 layers.
Top with fried onions (optional).
Bake 1 hour.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix sifted flour and salt in with butter and cheese.
Add cereal and mix well.
Form into small balls and flatten on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until edges begin to brown slightly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well, roll into round balls and put in cookie sheet. Bake at 400 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Mix potatoes, soup and milk in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. Add remaining ingredients.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sorry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Salt and fry hamburger until brown; add onions in hamburger while browning.
Mix remaining ingredients in the crock-pot.
Add browned hamburger and cook on low all day.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove leaves of cabbage.
Wash and immerse in boiling water. Cook 2 minutes.
Drain.
Combine meat, onion, pepper, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, garlic, butter and rice.
Spoon a portion of mixture onto each leaf.
Roll up.
Cover with water and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Arrange fruit alternately on toothpicks.

title: grandma's easy brisket
directions: Combine chili sauce, Coke and onion soup mix.
Pour over trimmed brisket and bake at 325° for 3 to 5 hours.
Drain fat from gravy.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt.
Mix cornstarch and water and pour into boiling mixture.
Cook until clear, at least 8 minutes, stirring all time.
Add
lemon juice and red cake coloring.
Fold in strawberries, then pour into crust which has been cooked, or use graham cracker crust.
Top with whipped cream and decorate with sliced strawberries.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix well the dark cherry Jell-O and boiling water. Then add orange juice, lemonade, sugar and cold water. Mix well and chill. Add 1-quart of ginger ale just before serving.

title: almost heaven cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prick hot cake with fork; pour pineapple over top.
Cool; leave in pan. Blend pudding and milk.
Add cream cheese slowly.
Spread this over the pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and decorate with nuts or coconut.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Refrigerate.
The longer this cake sets, the better it gets.

title: orange supreme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8 x 1 1/2-inch) layer pans.
Combine dry cake mix, coconut, 1 tablespoon orange peel, evaporated milk, 1/3 cup orange juice,
3 eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Mix cake as directed on package.
Divide batter evenly in pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans on racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool completely on racks.
Refrigerate cooled layers for ease in splitting.

title: mrs. griffin's persimmon pudding
directions: Press persimmons through a colander. Add sugar to persimmons. Then add milk, egg and dry ingredients. Bake in shallow pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onions in salted water until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly 1 hour.
Vary number of onions as desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour margarine in bottom of baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together and pour into baking dish.
Place fruit on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick "boiled" custard
directions: Mix pudding with milk; stir until dissolved.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Beat with rotary beater about 2 minutes.
Pour into a pitcher and refrigerate.

title: alice maxey's bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over cereal and sit aside.
In another bowl, cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to sugar and margarine mixture the flour mixture, cereal and buttermilk, alternately. Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 20 minutes.
Dough will keep 5 weeks in refrigerator.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in cold water.
Cream shortening.
Slowly add sugar and boiling water.
When cool, add yeast and well beaten eggs.
Add flour sifted with salt.
Mix thoroughly, preferably with dough hooks on electric mixer, but it can be done well mixed by hand.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lamb chops with lemon
directions: Trim excess fat from lamb chops.
Place in a single layer on a rimmed baking sheet.
Drizzle with 2 tablespoons of lemon juice. Sprinkle lightly with white pepper, then evenly with thyme. Refrigerate to blend flavors for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli in separate pans until done.
Drain and stir together in casserole dish.
Stir in undiluted soup.
Spoon Cheese Whiz around over top; do not stir in.
Bake at 350° until cheese is slightly brown.

title: chicken pot pie in a skillet
directions: Cook and dice chicken.
Return to skillet.
Add Veg-all and bouillon.
Cover and cook on medium until bouillon is dissolved. Serve with biscuits or alone.
Serves 2-4.

title: party sausage
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain off grease.
Add Velveeta; mix to blend.
Add spices and sauce.
Spread on party rye bread.
Place on cookie sheets and freeze.
Bake frozen at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.

title: pralines(blue ribbon winner at la paz county fair)
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, milk and margarine.
Place over high heat; stir constantly until boiling.
Reduce heat to medium and continue cooking to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, salt and pecans.
Beat until mixture just starts to thicken.
Drop onto waxed paper or lightly greased cookie sheet. Makes about 20.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and onions in layers with salt.
Cover with ice and put in refrigerator for 3 - 4 hours.
Drain.
Make syrup of vinegar, sugar, turmeric, mustard seed, and celery salt.
Add vegetables and heat slowly with very little stirring.
Scald, do not boil.
Place pickles in sterilized jars and seal.
Chill in refrigerator before serving for crispness.

title: spinach pie
directions: In a large bowl, mix eggs and cottage cheese.
Add flour, drained spinach and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place in greased deep dish pie plates and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken or turkey, celery, 1 cup of cheese, onion, seasoning and mayonnaise (to moisten good).
Mix lightly and put in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
While dish is baking, mix the crushed potato chips and the other cup of cheese. After has baked 45 minutes, spread crushed potato chips and cheese mix on top.
Put dish back in the oven and bake until the topping has fully melted (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir all together. Chill before serving.
This is excellent for all dipping.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in a saucepan. Cook until broccoli is tender. With remaining ingredients, make a white sauce. Cook on stove or in the microwave. Mix two together; heat and serve. Do not bring to a boil.

title: chess brownies
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add butter and egg yolks; mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover with confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop or break broccoli into small pieces and mix with raisins, cheese, pecan pieces and bacon bits.

title: stuffed ham rolls
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Drain juice from Mandarin oranges.
Combine juice, stuffing, chives and sage.
Roll each ham slice around some of the stuffing, using toothpicks to hold together.
Place rolls in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine marmalade, vinegar, mustard and orange slices.
Pour over rolls.
Bake in 400° oven for 14 minutes.

title: wedge baked potatoes
directions: Clean and cut into wedges 4 medium potatoes.
Sprinkle with pepper, paprika and a little salt.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.
Brush with light melted margarine.
Continue baking until done.
(May brush again if not a calorie counter.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine.
Put vanilla into margarine; let cool a little.
Place confectioners sugar and peanut butter in mixing bowl.
Pour the partially cooled margarine over sugar and peanut butter; mix well.
Knead like dough.
Place in long glass baking dish.
Press mixture very hard into baking dish until all dish bottom is covered and mixture is level.
Cut into serving squares.

title: lamb shanks
directions: Place shanks in roaster.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover. Bake 3 hours at 300°.
Remove cover.
Continue cooking for 30 minutes.
Pour sauce into saucepan.
Reduce to half over high heat.
Chill and remove fat.
Take meat off bones.
Add sauce. Heat.
Serve with rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain, mash and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until browned.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
If you do not want to use all of this at one time, roll into ball.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in freezer bags until ready to bake.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ham, pork, milk and eggs together well.
Add Wheaties and mix again.
To make individual loaves, use 3/4 to one cup of meat mixture per loaf.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Mix catsup, mustard and brown sugar well to make glaze.
Spread on top of hot loaves and bake about 1 minute more.
Makes about 30 loaves, depending on size.

title: quiche
directions: Crumble bacon on bottom of pie crust.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Add cheese.
Pour over bacon.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Can be mixed the night before and refrigerated.

title: fruit cobbler "any kind"
directions: Mix together and pour over fruit.
Add a little water.

title: dilled oyster crackers
directions: Combine oil, dressing, garlic powder, lemon pepper and dill weed in
a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Gradually add crackers to coat well.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and stir. Replace in oven for 5 minutes.
Place crackers on paper towel to cool.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a well-greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can be frozen and baked when needed.
Also nice served with fresh veggies.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Mix all together; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with one package stuffing mix.
Spread 3/4 cup melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fast chocolate-pecan fudge
directions: Microwave butter in 2 qt Micro-proof bowl at high (100%) for 1-1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Add cocoa, stir until smooth. Stir in confectioners sugar and vanilla, blend well.
(Mixture may be dry and crumbly.)
Stir in evaporated milk, microwave at high for one minute; stir.
Microwave an additional 1 minute or until mixture is hot.
Stir until smooth; add pecans.
Pour into foil lined 8 or 9 inch square pan.
Garnish with pecan halves, if desired.
Cover; chill until firm, about 1-2 hours.
Cut into 1 inch squares.
Store, covered in refrigerator.

title: chicken with balsamic vinegar
directions: Heat oil.
Add onions and garlic; saute about 4 minutes.
Add chicken; cook until brown, stirring often.
When brown, stir in vinegar and mustard.
Continue cooking for 3 minutes.
Season with salt, pepper and basil.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion over medium heat in large skillet; drain fat.
Add potatoes, tomato sauce and garlic salt.
Heat for 5 minutes.
Place in casserole.
Beat eggs in medium bowl; stir in yogurt.
Spread over meat mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cover bottom of baking pan with broccoli.
Layer chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Cover layer of chicken completely with mixture.
Layer cheese to cover.
Top off with croutons.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pluck-it cake
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in sugar, cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over biscuits after you put them in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: squash puff
directions: Cut squash and scoop out seeds.
Steam or bake in a 350° oven until tender.
Remove skin and mash.
Mix honey, flour, salt, spices and egg yolks.
Whip until blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into squash mix.
Pour into lightly oiled 1 1/2 quart dish.
Bake in a 350° oven until crusty, about 45 minutes.

title: simple peanut butter fudge
directions: Microwave frosting in a bowl for 1 minute on high. Microwave peanut butter for 1 minute on high. Mix the two together and add vanilla. Put in buttered tray and refrigerate for 4-5 hours.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine beef, onion, cracker crumbs, egg white, salt, pepper, milk, horseradish. Mix thoroughly. Shape into 4 oval 1/2 inch patties. Heat large non-stick skillet over medium heat until hot. Cook patties 7-8 minutes or until centers are no longer pink, turning once. Remove from skillet and keep warm. Add gravy to skillet and heat through. Serve steaks with gravy. Makes 4 servings.

title: aunt lavinia's award winning recipe - boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting when mixture reaches a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat well until blended.
Spoon onto waxed paper or foil.
Let cool for about 10 or 15 minutes.
Ready from start to finish in less than 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake angel food cake according to directions.
After cake has cooled, prepare pudding mix according to directions.
Alternate one layer of cake chunks, fresh sliced strawberries (already sweetened), pudding mix and crushed pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and decorate with whole strawberries.

title: crawfish or shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add flour and lightly brown it.
Add celery, green pepper and onion; cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add crawfish or shrimp tails.
Cover and cook 15 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, pepper and cayenne to taste.
Add onion tops and parsley.
Simmer a few minutes, covered, to blend seasonings.
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°. Grease and flour lightly a tube pan. Mix all above ingredients. Pour into pan and bake for 2 hours.

title: devil crabs
directions: Moisten toast with hot water.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well; pack in crab shells.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pancakes delicious
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a 10-inch skillet.
Simmer about 5 minutes on low heat.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine remaining ingredients except egg whites and sugar.
Beat egg whites and sugar together and fold into flour mixture.
Put apple slices in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and pour batter over.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add frozen strawberries.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts.
Pour half of jello mixture into Pyrex pan.
Chill until set; spread sour cream on that part, then add remaining jello mixture and refrigerate.

title: cinnamon bun cake
directions: Night Before:
Grease Bundt pan with butter (Pam).
Place pecans or walnuts on bottom of pan.
Layer Rich's dough balls. Sprinkle brown sugar.
Sprinkle pudding.
Sprinkle granulated sugar with cinnamon.
Melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine; put on top. Cover overnight with foil.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Bake potatoes on rack until tender, about 1 hour. Cool for 5 minutes. Reduce oven temp. to 350°. Horizontally cut off top third of each potato. Scoop out cooked potato, leaving 1/2 inch thick shell. In small skillet melt butter over medium heat. Add chives and garlic; cook until garlic softens, about 2 minutes. In large bowl mash cooked potato with garlic mixture, milk, parsley, salt and pepper until combined. Spoon or pipe mixture back into potato shells. Return to oven, bake until potatoes are browned and heated through, about 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg and drain grease.
Chop lettuce and tomatoes into small pieces.
Combine hamburg, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and Doritos in a large bowl, add dressing and mix well.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix in casserole dish; beat eggs well.
Stir in flour, sugar and salt.
Stir until blended.
Stir in corn.
Top with 1/2 cup crushed Ritz crackers and several pats of butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crabmeat sauce
directions: Mix crabmeat and shrimp cocktail sauce together.
Pour mixture over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple supreme cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box. Divide into two 9 x 13 inch cake pans. Bake as directed.
Mix vanilla pudding as directed on box. Add crushed pineapple then add cream cheese. Put filling on 1 1/2 of cake, top with other cake. Top entire cake with cool whip.

title: mashed potatoes deluxe
directions: Bring stock to boil in large pot.
Add potatoes.
Cover and return to boil for 15 minutes. Lower to medium-high heat, add carrots and onion.
Boil 20 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender. Drain potatoes, carrots and onion in colander.
Peel potatoes.
In large bowl, combine and mash peeled potatoes, carrots, onion, dill, butter, sour cream, parsley, salt and pepper.
Heat all ingredients thoroughly before serving.
Can be made ahead and microwaved.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: georgian pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Pour off excess fat.
Top pork chops with onion.
Mix rest of ingredients together and put over pork chops.
Cook slowly on top of stove for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: low calorie salad dressing
directions: Place ingredients in a blender and mix for 2 minutes or until smooth.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburg, sausage and onion. Boil noodles and drain.
Mix together with Prego.
Layer with pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Add Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix squash, green peppers, onion, pimentos and pickling salt and let sit overnight, then drain and rinse in cold water.
Bring 2nd part to a boil and add the 1st part.
Boil 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Place into jars and seal.

title: fruit and pecan balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and let it sit, stirring occasionally, for 1 hour.
Chop fine in a food processor.
Stir together the coconut, pecans and fruit mixture until it holds together.
Shape 1 teaspoon dough into ball and roll in sugar. Store in airtight container lined with wax paper; separate layers. Keeps a long time in a cool place.
Makes 36.

title: macaroni and tuna salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add all ingredients.
Add mayonnaise to moisten and season to taste.
Serve on lettuce or crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together well.
Drop on cookie sheet with spoon.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding small amounts of clam juice as needed to moisten.
Serve chilled with dipper chips, celery and/or simple crackers.
Sprinkle with paprika for color.

title: trifle
directions: Cube pound cakes; place on cookie sheet in oven at 300° for 1/2 hour, day before.
Store in dry place overnight.

title: sealy texas pecan pie
directions: Thoroughly beat
all
ingredients except eggs and nuts. Add eggs, beat gently until blended.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: red confetti ice
directions: Remove rind from orange and lemon.
Cut up the fruit; remove seeds.
Place orange, lemon and pineapple into blender.
Blend until pureed.
Add milk, corn syrup and 1 1/2 cups of water to mixture and blend well.
Stir in cherries.
Pour into a large freezer container.
Freeze until firm.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, beat until smooth, add remaining ingredients, stir.
Pour into lightly greased mold and freeze until set, 2 hours or longer.

title: summer's meat and potato casserole
directions: Combine the soup and the milk and then layer:
soup mix, cooked potatoes, meat, onion, fresh mushrooms and cheese slices. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves many.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Cut off root and tough leaves from leek.
Cut leek lengthwise in half; rinse to remove sand.
Cut leek into slices.
Peel and cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel, core and slice the apples. Cover with water and cook until soft. Add honey and spices. Cook until fairly thick.

title: danish open-faced sandwiches
directions: Peel onions and cut into thin slices.
Pour over boiling water and leave to cool.
Spread the bread thinly with butter and sprinkle over half of the dill.
Drain the sardines and arrange 2 on each piece of bread.
Cut the tomatoes into thick slices. Place the drained onion and tomato slices on the sardines and top with cucumber mixed with mayonnaise or sour cream, sugar and remaining dill.
Serves 4.

title: triple corn stew
directions: Coarsely chop or crumble sausage.
In a 4 to 5-quart pan over medium heat, stir sausage until well browned, 15 to 20 minutes. Discard drippings.
Add hominy, creamed corn and corn kernels. Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until hot, about 5 minutes. Mix cornstarch with broth.
Stir into pan and continue stirring until mixture boils.
Ladle stew into 4 wide bowls.
Garnish with radishes.
Serves 4.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Boil first 2 ingredients until sugar dissolves (just bring to a boil).
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, mix well.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch and chocolate chips on top.
Bake about 4 minutes at 350°.
Spread chips to cover top.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: mrs. andy granatelli's crisp toffee bars
directions: Adjust rack to center of oven.
In large bowl of electric mixer, cream butter.
Add salt, vanilla and brown sugar and beat well.
Add flour.
Add nuts and chocolate morsels.
Dough will be stiff.
With teaspoon or your fingers, place small mounds of dough in an unbuttered 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
With floured fingertips, press dough firmly to make even layer; it will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, reversing pan front to back to ensure even baking.
Cake will be golden brown.
Cool pan only a minute or so; cut into small bars.

title: coconut ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, then add milk and beat until fluffy.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add milk until freezer is 2/3 full and then freeze.

title: chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Keep hot.
Baste chicken or dip in sauce before they are put on grill.
Baste and turn at least four times.
Allow about 45 minutes cooking time.
Enough sauce for ten servings, 15 to 20 "parts" or 10 to 12 half chickens.

title: beef balls
directions: Thoroughly mix together all ingredients.
Form into balls about 1 1/2-inch in diameter.
Makes 24 to 28 balls.
Divide into 2 parts.
Slowly brown half the balls on all sides in 3 tablespoons fat.
Remove balls to hot platter.
Make gravy in same skillet.
At the same time, bake rest of beef balls in large casserole in moderate oven at about 350°.
Bake about 20 minutes; cool.
Cover and freeze or refrigerate until needed for other dishes.

title: purple cow
directions: You will need a blender, scoop, measuring cup and spoons and 2 glasses and straws.

title: cheesecake
directions: Melt butter and set aside.
Mix cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add flour and cornstarch.
Add butter and stir.
Fold in sour cream.
Bake in ungreased spring-form pan in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave cake in oven for 2 more hours.
Cool before cutting cake.
Time:
3 hours.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead until smooth.
You can leave overnight in refrigerator.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Let rise until nice and high, about 1 1/2 hours.
Make into 10 inch circle.
Butter each circle and cut in half.
Make 6 pie-shaped pieces.
Start from big end and roll into crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes

title: broiled peaches
directions: Arrange peach halves in a baking dish; fill each with 1 tablespoon concentrate and 1/2 teaspoon preserves.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and add remaining dry ingredients. Add shrimp and stir well to coat.
Divide shrimp on 6 (12 x 18-inch) pieces of heavy-duty foil.
Fold foil around shrimp, sealing edges well.
Grill over hot coals, about 8 minutes.
Turn and grill until done, about 6 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: lentil dip
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Drain.
Cook lentils in water until soft.
Drain.
Mash, cool and fry lentils with some butter. Mix lentils with ground beef.
Add taco mix.
Mix well.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients, blend well.
Add pumpkin and water, mix well.
Stir in floured raisins, if desired.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 400° for at least 30 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring to a boil. Add cucumbers. Bring to a boil. Seal in sterilized jars. Makes 3 quarts.

title: oatmeal carrot cookies
directions: Beat oleo 30 seconds.
Add half of flour, brown sugar, sugar, eggs, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, cloves and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour.
Add oats, carrots and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple glaze
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Use to glaze poultry or ham during roasting.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: apple cobbler for diabetics
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover bottom of an 8-inch Teflon coated pan with uncooked oatmeal.
Cover oatmeal with mixture of sliced apples, juice, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and honey.
Cover tightly with foil and bake for 1 hour.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle cobbler with cereal.
Bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: In a large skillet, over medium-high heat, cook the ground beef, onion and garlic, stirring often to break up lumps, until the meat loses its pink color, about 5 minutes.

title: hearty italian bean soup
directions: Cut ham into pieces.
Dice celery, carrots, onion and zucchini.
In a 5-quart saucepot, add all ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken broth, spinach, beans and 2 cups water.
Cook over low heat.
Makes 5 main-dish servings, about 240 calories, 6 g fat, 9 mg cholesterol.

title: zucchini bundt cake
directions: Mix well, then pour half of mixture into greased and floured Bundt or angel food pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Pour rest of batter on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pita pizza
directions: In skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, cook onion, green pepper and Italian seasoning until tender-crisp.
Add tomatoes; cook and stir for five minutes.
Cut pitas in half horizontally, making 2 flat circles.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cheese on each pita half.
Top with tomato mixture, then remaining cheese.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and mold
into
a rounded flat loaf. Spread 2 tablespoons or more ketchup
on
top and bake 15 to 20 minutes on High in microwave oven.

title: devin's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Bake three layers.
Cool cake completely.
Spread the Cool Whip between the layers.
Frost cake with your favorite chocolate icing.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with Marshmallow Creme and lime juice.
Serve with assorted fruits.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine finely ground tomatoes, celery, onions and salt; put in cheesecloth bag to drain overnight.
Next morning, combine vinegar, sugar, pepper and spices together.
Boil vinegar solution altogether for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes from cheesecloth; stir well and bring to rolling boil for 20 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: turkey noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and mix well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese and bake about 5 minutes longer.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Stir over low heat. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes (to a soft ball stage). Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate and vanilla until chocolate is melted.
Pour into a buttered pan.

title: dijon marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.

title: "beary" good snack mix
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Store in a Ziploc bag or a covered container.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Flour and grease coffee cans.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake until done.

title: salad dressing i
directions: Bring
to a boil the vinegar and water.
Add milk and bring back to a boil.

title: greek eggplant moussaka
directions: Peel eggplants; slice into rounds 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle both sides with salt.
Place in a deep bowl.
Cover with cold water.
Place plate on top to keep slices submerged.
Let stand 1 hour.
When ready to use, rinse and drain.
Saute meat in butter until color is gone.
Add onion; cook until soft.
Drain off fat. Mix in tomato sauce, water, parsley, all spice and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, until liquid is absorbed.
Cool 30 minutes.
Beat eggs to a froth.
Stir into meat.
Add Parmesan cheese, 3 tablespoons bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs on bottom of dish.
Arrange 1/3 eggplant slices over crumbs.
Cover with meat mixture.
Add another layer of eggplant slices, then rest of meat.
Top with eggplant slices.
Pour Moussaka Sauce over all.
Bake 1 hour at 375° or until set.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes.

title: chopped chicken liver pate
directions: Cook livers 5 to 10 minutes (can do eggs at same time); start with cold water.
Blend all ingredients, except butter or margarine, in blender until smooth.
Add butter and blend again. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: pinto beans with meat
directions: Look through the beans and pick out all the rocks and rotten looking beans.
Throw that away and wash the good ones at least 2 or 3 times with clean water.
Don't leave any of those beans in my sink for me to have to clean out later.
Drain all the water out and put the beans in a large pot.
Fill it almost to the top with cold water.
Add your cut up meat to the pot.
Bring it to a boil. Cut down to about medium heat and cook until done, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Season with salt and simmer until you're ready to eat.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: Mix in order given, stir until sugar is dissolved. Pour into gallon-sized ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: french chocolate mint pie
directions: Combine crumbs, melted butter and powdered sugar.
Firmly press over bottom and up sides of 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Place in freezer while preparing filling.

title: buttermilk cornmeal pancakes
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Mix together the buttermilk, egg and vegetable oil.
Combine wet and dry ingredients; cook on griddle.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: easy apple or peach cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend together cake mix, eggs and pie filling in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Spread half of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of sugar and cinnamon over batter. Repeat with rest of batter and remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until pick comes out clean.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Add all ingredients, except raisins and pecans, in a large mixing bowl and mix well.
Bake at 325° in 13 x 9-inch cake pan for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Serve plain or with icing.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice over bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Layer sausage over rice and onion over sausage.
In separate bowl, mix water and soups; pour over rice and sausage.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts in bottom of pan.
Spread coconut over nuts.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box. Pour over coconut.
Soften oleo and cream cheese; add confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Pour on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake separates from pan.
Looks like an earthquake hit it, but very delicious.
They will want seconds.

title: apricot salad
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil jello, water and sugar.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese, baby food and pineapple.
Whip evaporated milk until stiff.
Fold cold mixture into whipped milk. Add pecans and mix.
Pour into dish and sprinkle with a few finely chopped pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: spicy black-eyed peas
directions: Cook the black-eyed peas, vegetables and seasonings, all in a large pot.
Bring the mixture to a rolling boil, then reduce heat. Simmer for 2 hours, adding water if needed.
The pot should have a heavy lid.
This dish is excellent to serve with hot cornbread.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Mix dates, flour, milk, 1 cup brown sugar and baking powder and place in 8-inch pan.
Mix white sugar and 1/4 cup packed brown sugar and sprinkle mixture evenly over top of dough. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and nuts.
Over this pour the boiling water.
Bake at 375° until thick (30 minutes.)

title: baked egg casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan; line pan with bread cubes. Combine eggs, salt, mustard and milk.
Pour over bread; let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake covered for 50 minutes at 350°; uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: hot taco rice
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Add salsa.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare rice as directed.
Serve beef mixture over rice.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well and add salt.
Prepare salad by tearing lettuce into bite size pieces in a very large bowl.
Add onion, tomatoes, cheese, corn chips and meat to salad.
Pour dressing over mixture and toss to combine.
Garnish with additional corn chips, tomato slices and shredded cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix liquids.
Pour in pie crust.
Freeze.
Use yellow or pink food coloring for color.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all together well.
Form into ball.
Roll into a ball. Roll in finely chopped pecans; chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: chilli-cheesy-rice pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In	medium	saucepan,
mix rice and soup. Put in greased
9-inch
pie pan; press firmly to bottom and sides to form crust.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in skin.
Cool.
Skin potatoes.
Add butter and mash.
Add sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flavoring.
Add cinnamon, more or less to taste, and salt. Pour into 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Add marshmallows to top and continue baking until brown.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Peel peaches and set aside.
Mix all ingredients except peaches.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add peaches; churn until frozen.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: liver fries
directions: Cook
meat
and drain grease.
Saute onions, mushrooms, green pepper
and
garlic.
Add
meat, except sausage (you can cut up some of the link sausage, but leave some whole to go on top
for decoration).
Add
eggs
and
cubed cheese, stirring occasionally. When
almost
done,
add
tomatoes.
Put sliced cheese
on
top and remove from fire; cover.
Add hot coals on top
of
lid.
Cook until cheese is melted and slightly brown. Place remaining sausage on top.
Serve with toast and salsa.

title: oriental beef and noodle toss
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, brown ground beef over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
Break into 3/4-inch crumbles.
Remove meat with slotted spoon; drain off drippings.
Season beef with 1 packet seasoning from Ramen noodle package; set aside.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar mixture.
Combine applesauce, cake mix and eggs in mixer bowl.
Mix using package directions.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Set aside.
Mix flour, soda and salt together.
Add flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal, raisins, coconut and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into small balls, about 1 teaspoon size.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.

title: grandma beth's salsa
directions: Chop everything and mix well. Chill for 1 hour.

title: josefinas(spanish pizza)
directions: Cut loaf of bread in half lengthwise, then crosswise into serving size pieces.
Mix chilies, butter and garlic.
Spread on bread.
Top with mixture of the mayonnaise and cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven until bubbly.
Serve at once.
Yields 24 servings.

title: grandmother's best baked beans
directions: Bring beans and 6 cups water to boil in a heavy 3 to 4-quart pot over high heat.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain.
Add 6 cups fresh water and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour or until beans are almost tender.
Drain.
Heat oven to 350°. Mix broth, tomato sauce, molasses, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and celery salt in a deep 3-quart casserole.
Gently stir in beans, onion, bacon and apple.
Cover and bake 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Uncover and bake 1 hour longer until sauce has thickened and top is browned.
Makes 7 cups.

title: chicken breasts in lemon cream sauce
directions: Lightly salt and pepper chicken breasts.
Melt butter in skillet and saute chicken for 5 to 8 minutes, turning once to cook on all sides.
Place chicken in ovenproof serving dish.
Add lemon juice to butter in skillet.
Stir cornstarch into cream and slowly add it into skillet mixture, stirring constantly, on low heat. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and broil until golden brown. Good with rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit bars
directions: Mix above ingredients well.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Break angel food cake up into pieces and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour over cake.
Mix bananas, pineapple (drain half the juice) and strawberries. Put on top of cake. Spread Cool Whip over top. Refrigerate.

title: soup
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add water to obtain desired thickness.
Cook about 2 hours until meat is tender.
Salt to taste.
Add potatoes and cook until potatoes are done.
Can also be made in crock-pot.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Saute celery, carrots and onions in butter until tender. Add soup, broth, parsley
and
hot
pepper
sauce.
Simmer
20 minutes.
Add milk; heat.
Just before serving, stir in cheese. Do not boil.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: baked ham
directions: Score and place whole cloves in ham.
Cover with
a mixture of spicy mustard and brown sugar.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 7 hours or until nice and brown and crispy.

title: egg toast
directions: Beat the egg thoroughly and add the salt and milk.
Have the bread cut in thin slices.
Dip them in the milk, allowing each to absorb some.
Brown in a buttered frying pan or on a griddle. Butter and serve hot with sugar and cinnamon or syrup.

title: layered salad
directions: Shred lettuce in bowl.
Place drained peas over lettuce.
Layer with green pepper, onions, mayonnaise, eggs, bacon and cheese.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar until smooth.
Add yeast, then add 1 cup warm milk.
Add 4 cups flour.
Mix well and set aside to rise for 2 hours.
Melt butter.
Dump dough on floured board and divide into 2 portions.
Roll dough and cut into slices. Dip strips of dough into melted butter and layer into tube pan (or may place loaf of dough, dipped in butter, in a tube pan). Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes.
Mix in Cheez Whiz.
Put potatoes into a greased casserole dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Cut off top loaf (about 1/3) and hollow out remainder.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fill hollow in bread with above mixture and wrap in foil (do not put top on the bread).
Bake 3 hours at 250°.
Cut top and bread from center of loaf into small pieces for dippers.
You will also need an extra loaf to cut for dippers. Later, break off pieces of the loaf itself.
Eat the whole thing!

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown meat; add all ingredients. Mix well and place in baking dish (9 x 13-inches). Top with can of Chinese noodles. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Serves 8.

title: potato bake
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Fold all ingredients into a large bowl. Spoon mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: coriander bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water; add a pinch of sugar to make sure it bubbles and yeast is active.
In large bowl, combine yeast mixture, warm milk, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, clove, coriander and oil.
Stir in pureed orange and egg and work in flour 1 cup at a time.
When dough becomes too stiff to work with a spoon, turn out on floured board.
Knead in as much flour as it will take. Dough will be very smooth.
Rinse bowl and oil it lightly.
Ball up the dough and place in bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and put it in a warm place to rise.
When doubled in bulk punch down and divide into 2 and shape into loaves.
Cover and let rise again until almost doubled.
Brush tops with egg wash and bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: layered tortilla pie(mexican casserole)
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, olives, chili powder, salt and pepper.
In a round 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over top.
Pour water at edge of casserole into bottom.
Cover and bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Uncover; let stand for 5 minutes before cutting into wedges. Serves 4.

title: ice cream icing
directions: Mix together until creamy.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 3 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: sugarless applesauce fruit cake
directions: *BLKLIN steeped in hot water for 20 minutes, strained and applied in compress form to the eyes for imflammation or congestion (puffiness).
Refrigerate and use cold tea twice a day for refreshing and toning of the skin tissue around the eyes.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Bring cabbage, bean sprouts and celery to a boil, then drain. Stir-fry chicken for 3 minutes.
Add water chestnuts, garlic and soy sauce to chicken and stir-fry for 5 minutes more.
Mix fried and boiled vegetables (you can add more soy sauce if needed).
Let stand for a few minutes.
Roll into skins; seal with beaten egg. Deep-fry until crisp.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion, water and margarine until tender.
Add eggs, milk, cheese and crackers; mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake at 325° until top is slightly browned.

title: banana nut bread #2
directions: Mix in order given. Add soda to sour milk.
Mash bananas thoroughly before adding to mixture. Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Use two loaf pans.

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
If desired, may cover with slivered almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use loaf pan.
